1.description: You are standing in a high stone cavern with a large exit to the west. To the north is a small round opening in the wall with large bright neon letters abov e it reading : SANTA'S GROTTO

2.description: You are in dark desolate dismal room.

5.description: The sound of rapidly moving water can be heard from a very small hole in the floor at the back of the room, but nothing can be seen down it. The room is littered with empty barrels and appears to have been a store room formerly.

6.description: The sound of rapidly moving water can be heard from a very small hole in the floor at the back of the room, but nothing can be seen down it. The room is littered with empty barrels and appears to have been a store room formerly.

8.description: This room, unlike the one you have left, is merely a cave hewn roughly out of the rock. The walls are damp and there is evidence of recent attempts at tunnelling.

9.description: Many decades ago, this large circular room was of great importance, but its beauty has diminished. Many of the tall stone pillars are now lopsided, and an evil-smelling yellow fungus lines the walls.

11.description: This room is filled with a red light, but you cannot detect where it is coming from. On the North wall, someone has chalked : 'HAS ANYONE SEEN A GUIDE ?'

12.description: This room is filled with a red light, but you cannot detect where it is coming from. On the North wall, someone has chalked : 'HAS ANYONE SEEN A GUIDE ?'

13.description: aper/A newspaper/A n You are in a decrepit storeroom. The floor is covered with rubbish.

14.description: aper/A newspaper/A n You are in a decrepit storeroom. The floor is covered with rubbish.

15.description: Daylight enters the room from a hatch in the ceiling.The room is filled with large piles of leaves,twigs,and ripped up copies of the dungeon sun...... rustling noises appear from under the trash.

16.description: Daylight enters the room from a hatch in the ceiling.The room is filled with large piles of leaves,twigs,and ripped up copies of the dungeon sun...... rustling noises appear from under the trash.

17.description: This small room is lit by two torches set in the walls. A table and chair stan din the centre of the room, and a place has been laid at the table, but there i s no food in sight. On the floor in the corner is a straw mattress.

18.description: This small room is lit by two torches set in the walls. A table and chair stan din the centre of the room, and a place has been laid at the table, but there i s no food in sight. On the floor in the corner is a straw mattress.

19.description: You are in a small room. There is a door in the east wall but it appears to be locked. Three other corridors leave the room. There is a blackboard on the wall. ./

20.description: You are in a new cave.

21.description: You crawl into a tiny hole littered with droppings and blood. The stench of lizard is overpowering. Through the thick gloom you can just make out a notice 'TO THE ISLAND' hanging above a blue teleport gate in the east wall.

22.description: You crawl into a tiny hole littered with droppings and blood. The stench of lizard is overpowering. Through the thick gloom you can just make out a notice 'TO THE ISLAND' hanging above a blue teleport gate in the east wall.

23.description: You are in a hallway cut out from the rock. Candles provide a pleasant glow and there are lots of pictures of farmyard scenes on the walls. Several side table s are stacked with cheap china. The whole room exudes friendliness and domestic ity

24.description: You are in a hallway cut out from the rock. Candles provide a pleasant glow and there are lots of pictures of farmyard scenes on the walls. Several side table s are stacked with cheap china. The whole room exudes friendliness and domestic ity

25.description: You are in a small, gloomy cave. As your eyes get accustomed to the darkness yo unotice several suspiciously large bones strewn around. The wooden tables and chairs are badly gnawed and there is an unpleasant stench of rotting meat.

26.description: You are in the hobbit's lounge. A small fire burns merrily in the corner and there are several battered wooden chairs. The room smells strongly of pine needles and there are a few exotic pot plants. ./

27.description: You come to a sharp turn in the corridor. The light here is very dim and you notice a peculiar smell, but you cannot tell where it is coming from.

29.description: You come into a small room. Nailed to the south wall is a crude wooden rack, presumably for torches.

30.description: You are in a large cavern with a high ceiling. Thousands of bats hang from the ceiling and walls and the floor in ankle deep in their droppings. There is a crudely lettered board by a narrow tunnel to the north - 'NO HEWMANS OR UTHER HORID THINGS'

31.description: You are in another cavern. The floor is covered in pools of stagnant water and stinking mud. Someone has floored the room with wooden planks long ago, but no w they are rotten and collapsing.

32.description: You are in a small musty cave. It is very muddy and green slime seeps down the walls. The cave continues to the west but the ceiling is too low to allow you through.

33.description: You are walking down a very long, narrow corridor. There are so many twists and turns that you quickly forget which direction you are going. There are several webbed footprints in the mud. There is a crude wooden noticeboard on the wall .

34.description: You are in a tiny room. 'LIZID'S LAIR - GO AWAY' has been obliterated from the floor and a neat notice on the wall reads 'COLONY OF DRAVAKIAN EMPIRE'. A human skeleton is chained to the wall

35.description: You are in the lizard men's sleeping quarters. There are several wooden bunks, and there is a large cooking pot filled with an evil smelling liquid.

36.description: You are in the lizard men's cooking quarters. There is an evil smelling cooking pot here.

37.description: You are in a well room. Burning torches provide a poor light, but apart from th ewell itself (built crudely from stone) and a broken bucket, it is empty. Spilt water has collected into puddles in the uneven floor.

38.description: You are in some sort of store room. Rickety shelves are lined with rusted spear sbleached skulls, lumps of clay and rotted clothing. It is very humid and water drips slowly from the roof.

39.description: You are in a round cave, with wooden benches all round the walls. A heavy oak door to the west is locked with an enormous padlock. 'KEPE OUT' has been carve d in the wood.

40.description: This room has been recently renovated (shock horror of all things!). Luxurious curtains and expensive wall hangings line the walls now. Best of all there is a glowing blue portal to the north.

41.description: You are in a large corridor. There is a notice board here.

42.description: You are in the main corridor. The wa,lls here are slightly pitted and blackened .A wide opening has been cut in the south wall. 'STORAGE' is printed over it.

46.description: You are in a room on the edge of the temple. One of the walls has collapsed, an dthe place is in a generally bad state of repair. A ruined altar stands in the middle of the room with the words 'God dusnt ecsist' written on it in bright red

47.description: You are in a waiting room. There is a queue of people along one wall, and above the door to the east is a sign saying "Last stop to Squirgle Buven". There is a table against another wall with a pile of forms on it.

48.description: You are at a strange place. The atmosphere is tense, and green light shines fro mthe edges of the main, locked, door. You hear a voice boom "AND LET THAT BE A LESSON !" from within. There is a counter in the corner with a sign : "Apply fora ticket !".

49.description: There used to be something to do with a large plant in the middle of this cave, but it has since rotted away to a short brown stalk. There is a sign saying 'G o up to the Library - Show your ticket'.

50.description: Youa are in a very blank room. The floor is blank, the walls are blank, the c ceiling is blank, even the blank thing in the corner is blank.

51.description: You are in a passage leading up to the throne room of the Tauyon Temple Mission .Candles flicker in the slight breeze of your passing, and the shadows dance among the stone pillars which stretch up high into the dome.

52.description: You are in the throne room of the Mission. Sneering stone gargoyles look down from the ceiling and a vast portrait shows a hooded monk slaying a wolf. There is an enormous marble throne in the middle of the room.

53.description: You are in the main corridor which runs east-west. There is a jagged, gaping hole hacked in the south wall, but it is too dark to see inside it, although i t smells unpleasantly of rotting vegetation.

54.description: You are in a small cave which has many leaves and other rustling things on the floor, in great heaps. There are openings to the north and west.

55.description: You are in some sort of prayer cell. It is very severely decorated, with only a stone seat and a straw mattress. A sign hung on the wall reads : 'GLORY TO TAUYON'

56.description: You are at the end of the main corridor. There is a bell on the wall. A large wooden door stands slightly ajar, and printed on it in neat capitals is : 'DRAGONEWTS. NO FIGHTING. NO ADVENTURERS. NO KIDDING.'

57.description: You are in a large hallway which has a long passage leading south. It is quite dilapidated and the, roof sags and seems to have collapsed in some places. Further along there seems to be a crossroads.

58.description: You are in a wide, cold hallway lit by flickering torches. It has been propped up in several places where the roof has collapsed. There is a T-junction just ahead. ./

59.description: You are in a stone room with low benches and a wooden table. There are some unpleasant-looking racks and a brazier with a red-hot pincer resting on it. There is a black hole cut in the north wall.

60.description: You are in a luxurious room, with plush red satin cushions. Expensive pictures line the walls, and a cocktail cabinet sits in one corner.

61.description: You are at a crossroads. A signpost points 'East to the Deserted Passage', 'Wes tto the Gates of Moria' and 'North to the Pub'.

62.description: There are several wooden chairs and tables in this room, but they have been badly damaged by a recent rock fall. Water drips slowly from wide cracks in th e ceiling.

63.description: You are in a large bare hall with a high, vaulted roof. There is a heavy iron door to the east, but it stands wide open. A message is carved above the door: 'Entrance to Dungeon. Please seek permission before re-entering .'

64.description: You are in a general dining/living area. There is a small kitchen with a wood fire, some greasy tables and chairs, and a target practice board with yellow a ndblack rings. Huge sides of meat hang in an alcove near the kitchen.

65.description: You are in a hallway. To the east, a wooden door is covered in unreadable graffiti, and a heavy iron door to the south marked 'TREASURY' is locked.

66.description: You are in the Treasury. It is very gloomy and sheets hang over the walls. Empt ywooden chests are stacked up in a corner, and there are several books and documents and worthless trinkets on shelves.

67.description: You are in a lecture theatre with rows of benches grouped around a central platform. There is a wall map, but you cannot work out what it shows.

68.description: onds You are in a small, smoky room with a large wooden table. There are several empty beer glasses, mouldy sandwiches and playing cards scattered on the floor .

69.description: You are in a small, smoky room with a large wooden table. There are several empty beer glasses, mouldy sandwiches and playing cards scattered on the floor .

70.description: You are in a crudely cut tunnel. Sharp spikes of rock stick out and the floor i swet and muddy. There is a small hole, just big enough to squeeze through, in t hesouth wall.

71.description: This room is very cold, although there is a fire in a small grate. The roof is very high above, and you can just see some moving black shapes. Strangely,ther e is a carcass in the middle of the floor.

72.description: The tunnel widens slightly into a corridor which runs east-west. The walls are built from a strange red rock.

73.description: You are in a passageway. 'MAIN THROUGH ROUTE' is carved on the wall, but really it is little more than a tunnel. The passage runs east-west, and high up on th e wall there is a hole.

74.description: You are in a small shrine within the crack. Light comes from a glowing green fungus growing on the wall. Water drips into a small pool in the corner of thi s rough hewn chamber.

75.description: You are somewhere i am sure.

76.description: You are in a large cavern which rises high overhead. A hand-carved archway lead sto the east where a tombstone can be glimpsed. The main passage is to the nort h through a thin crack in the wall.

77.description: You are in another cavern. Marble steps lead down into a central area, where there is a statue and a tombstone. On the tombstone is written: 'ALDRED WILL RISE AGAIN'

78.description: You are in a chapel. There is a stone bowl filled with blood, with stone wolves drinking from it. VENGEANCE is written in foot high letters on the wall. 'Gerbil - No entry' is on a shiny door to the south.

79.description: You are in another hall. Most of it is buried in huge piles of rubble from a recent rock fall. A marble pillar leans over at a crazy angle, and part of a chandelier sticks out from the rubbish.

80.description: You are in a wide high corridor, which runs into a cavern to the south. Painted in giant letters on the floor is 'SHOUT PASSWERD BEFORE PROSEEDING'. To the north, a door stands open.

81.description: You are in an office. There is a desk, a swivel chair and a green carpet. A pleasant countryside scene is visible out of the window. A bright poster above the desk reads :'JOIN FRIENDS OF THE GERBIL TODAY!'

82.description: You are in the main passageway. It continues east and west.

83.description: You are at the end of the passageway. To the east is a rusted iron door with a bell and to the south a wooden door is marked 'ViLLIj'. Loud noises can be hea rdfrom the south.

84.description: You are in a large rough walled cave, lit by a large torch on the east wall. To the west the is small slot, into which things could be dropped.

85.description: As you walk into this damp room, a strange green mist swirls around your ankles You notice, to your horror, that there is a slightly decayed corpse hanging fr oma noose, an indescribable look of terror on its face.

86.description: You are standing on a raised walkway around a grating set into the floor.

87.description: You are in a high-ceilinged though quite narrow cavern. A sign above a button i nthe wall reads 'DO NOT PRESS THIS BUTTON'.

88.description: ap~400/Key 68 You are a circular room with plush velvet covers lining the walls.

89.description: You are at a bend in a corridor, which runs north and west. There is a small, locked door in the east wall.

90.description: A green slime grows over the walls here, and seems to be entering from a small roughly hewn arch to the east. There is a notice board on one wall.

92.description: You are in the most exotic room in the dungeon. Portraits of old System Managers are hung all around, plus one of Mohit, which is seems to be being used as a dart board. This room also holds a secret, and only a few know of i t.

93.description: elled gold bracelet~ The floor here slopes down to the west and ends in a vertical drop.

94.description: You are in a long room with a wooden floor and ceiling. Bunks are stacked up three high on the walls and the air is stale and smells strongly of tobacco. There are crude drawings and graffiti all over the walls.

95.description: You are in a huge cavern, the roof is out of sight overhead. A strange soft glo wseems to emanate from the rock, for there are no other sources of light. In th e centre of the cavern is a vast shrine, with intricate crystal and stone arche s.

96.description: You are at the bottom of a large pit. Water falling from above swirls around your broken legs and exits down a small hole. There is no way out.

97.description: You are at the western end of a large, airy corridor. Along the south wall ther eare several locked iron doors. A sign reads: 'These rooms are available to the public for storage. The Management accepts no responsibility for any loss or damage.'

98.description: You are in a small cave, which used to be a store room. Howver, it has been pillaged, and the secrets of the room stolen.

99.description: You are in the demi-god's office. A bottle of Chateau Lafite '59 lies in the corner, in a pool of discarded vomit. On the record player is a copy of Led Ze p III, the basic signs of a good party.

100.description: You are in a long corridor.

101.description: You are in a long tunnel

102.description: You are in a large cave like room.

103.description: CENTRAL DUNGEON FOOD STORAGE.TYPE 'YUMMY' for food.

104.description: CENTRAL DUNGEON SECONDARY WEAPONS STORE. Store minor weapons only here, powerful weapons should be moved to the primary store.

106.description: Room 106 - key and general storage. Keys 680,682,684 and 686 are for the hotel guest rooms. Key 688 is a covienient exit, key 697 is for the island treasure store.

107.description: CENTRAL DUNGEON DISTRIBUTION CENTRE. This comunicates with Store rooms.

108.description: You enter throught the steel panel. You feel dizzy from your previous experienc e and fall throught a hole in the Sphinxs' Head.

109.description: After you realize your stupid mistake you walk off the Sphinx's Head !!! You ar e you are in the cavity that used to be the Sphinx's nose.

110.description: You are in between the paws of the Sphinx. It's paws look invitingly soft. Here is a chance to leave this doomed area.

111.description: You are buried deep under the sand of the desert, looking for the lost city of GOLD. Noone has ever found this fantastic city.

112.description: You are in the Sand, Deep under the Pyramids.

113.description: You fall into a valley of wonder, the home of the golden citizens, THE LOST CIT Y OF GOLD !!!

115.description: Key/Key nothing/Ske An exit key store initiated by Nargothron the Mage

120.description: You are standing at an intersection. Two well-lit corridors lead east and south ,and a set of dark, narrow steps lead downwards to the west.

121.description: You are in a round cave with three exits.

122.description: The corridor turns here, but in the corner is a small pool of water with strange coloured rocks at the bottom....REREAD THIS DESCRIPTION PLEBS.

123.description: You walk down the steps. A passage leads on for about 20 metres, then some step slead up at the far end. Pools of water are underfoot and you have to stoop to avoid hitting your head on the low ceiling.

124.description: You are standing in a well-lit corridor running north-south. A flight of damp, narrow steps leads down to the east.

125.description: You are at an intersection of a long corridor running north-south with a corridor running west. Not far down the passage west you can see a door.

126.description: You are in a corridor running north-south. There is a door in the west wall.

127.description: You are in a corridor running east-west. In front of you, in the south wall, there is a door.

128.description: As you walk down the corridor, you pass a section of wall that is covered in painted graffiti. Most of them seem to be complaining about the standard of th e accommodation.

129.description: Walking down the corridor, you come to a door in the north wall. Scratched into it are some odd symbols that you have not seen before. To the west, the corrid orturns left.

130.description: You are in a small, bare room. A particularly evil-looking face has been carve dinto the south wall.

131.description: You are in a corridor running north-south. Looking north, you see that the corridor turns right. Looking south, the corridor gets very narrow.

132.description: You open the door, and step into a dark room. Suddenly the floor gives way and you fall down about 20 feet into an earthy hole. Next to you you notice another hole, which appears to be the only way out. Type 'W' to jump.

133.description: You walk down the corridor that gets progressively narrower, until you are forced to walk sideways.

134.description: You are in a low corridor. To the north, the corridor narrows. To the south, you can see a junction.

135.description: You fall down about 15 feet into a bigger cavern. It is pitch black, but you manage to feel your way around the side to a small tunnel leading off to the south.

136.description: As you crawl down the tunnel, you notice that it is getting steeper. The tunnel is too narrow for you to turn round and too steep for you to crawl backwards - you must go on.

137.description: You arrive at a branch in the tunnel. You must choose carefully because you will not be able to turn round !

138.description: As you crawl down the tunnel, you suddenly fell the earth give way and the floo rstarts to slide away from you.

139.description: As you crawl west along the dark tunnel, you suddenly come up against a hard ro cky surface. However, you find a small lever, which when pulled, opens a secret door into a bright corridor. Someone has added an extra GOLD lever.

140.description: You have fallen into a cavern and rocks are falling all around. There is no way out !

141.description: You walk north down the corridor and come to a wooden door.

142.description: You enter a small hallway. In front of you is a door marked 'THE ROYAL HOTEL' You open the door and peer round. In a small, damp, bare room stands a man. He is muttering about the room service, clearly he has been conned.

143.description: You are in a small, damp, bare room. There is a door in the south wall.

144.description: You leave and walk back down the well-lit corridor.

145.description: You are standing at a bend in the wide corridor, which runs north and west.

146.description: You are in a corridor running east-west. There is a door in the north wall.

147.description: You walk into a small room, full of large wooden boxes, one of which seems to b ethe lair of some creature.

149.description: You are standing at the junction of a wide, well-lit corridor running east-west and a smaller one running north. The passage leading west turns north after 40 feet.

154.description: You stand in a dry corridor a brightly lit junction greets your eyes to the South.A message is scrawled on the wall......in blood!

155.description: Two dingy corridors meet the one in which you walk,an evil feeling accompanies this place,chilling your heart.Straining your ears you imagine that you can hear creatures moving in the dark.

156.description: You enter a small dark room, the floor is covered in old bones and other rubbis hand the ceiling is very low.

157.description: You are in a dark corridor running east-west. In the south wall of the passage there is an opening leading to a narrow, earthy passage.

159.description: You seem to have entered the lair of some creature.

160.description: You are in a large, dark cave. You can hear a noise which sounds like many flie sbuzzing, but cannot tell from which direction it is coming.

161.description: You are in a small room with a shaft going upwards in the centre. No light come sfrom it, however, and the only exits are a corridor going off to the east and a door in the south wall.

162.description: You stand in an enourmous cavern.A giant silver lever projects up out of the floor.A sign states 'PULL OR ---'.

163.description: You are in a set of earthy tunnels. Nearby is a small hole which you can just see (or put your hand) into.

164.description: You are in a small, bare room.

165.description: You are at a bend in a dark corridor which goes north and west. Not far away, there is a hole in the eastern wall. You can crawl into it if you wish.

166.description: You are at the end of a long passage which leads off to the west. A few paces to the south is the entrance to a large cavern.

167.description: You are in a small, dismal room with an evil-smelling fungus on the floor. There is a door in the north wall.

168.description: You are in a slimy hole.

169.description: You are in a dark corridor running east-west. It is very damp.

170.description: This room appears to have a single exit,and you have just used it.A triangular hole is cast into a metal wall to the North.It seems that someone has been been investigating before you arrived.

172.description: You are in a large earthy cavern.

173.description: You stand at the intersection of four passages....crumbs litter the floor here below the wheel set into the wall.

174.description: You are in an earthy cavern, but it is empty.

175.description: The tunnel comes to a dead end.

176.description: You are in a small round hole

178.description: The tunnel ends in a dry, sandy cavity.

179.description: You are in a large earthy cavern.

180.description: You are walking in a long passageway. Clammy smells make you cough and splutter .

181.description: You are at a bend in a tunnel, which runs north and west.

183.description: You are in a small rocky cave. Two narrow tunnels lead out to east and west. On a wall, someone has scratched : GIANT INSECTS - BEWARE !

184.description: You are at the intersection of four tunnels.

185.description: You are at a bend in the tunnel, which runs west and north.

186.description: You are in a small cavern.

187.description: This is an uncharacteristically large cavern/corridor there is/are some/one esi t....yes another corrupt room... any useful descriptions please send to OSTROGO TH

188.description: You are in a small cavern with three exits.

189.description: You are in a cavern with three exits.

190.description: You seem to have entered the lair of some creature.

191.description: You are in a low, narrow tunnel.

192.description: You are in a small cave with rocky ledges around the walls that you can use for a seat.

193.description: You are in a small earthy hole.

194.description: The tunnel comes to an abrupt end.

195.description: The tunnel twists and turns - you cannot tell which way it is leading.

196.description: You are in a large cave, with two earthy tunnels leading out. The tunnel leadin geast soon turns south, and the one leading west soon turns north.

197.description: You are in a large cavern with four exits. The floor is covered with bones and chewed pieces of meat, and the stench is almost overpowering.

198.description: You are in an earthy cavern. There are many tiny holes in the walls, but you cannot tell what they are for, or who made them.

199.description: You are at the intersection of four earthy tunnels.

200.description: You are at a bend in an earthy tunnel. It leads west and south.

201.description: You are in a damp, muddy cave. You can hear water dripping somewhere, and the floor and walls are very sticky.

202.description: You are in a small cave. There are some stools in the middle of the floor, but no table, and you cannot see any other sign of habitation.

203.description: You are at a bend in a low tunnel.

205.description: You are in a dark corridor running east-west. To the west the corridor is flooded, but you cannot tell how deep it is from here.

206.description: The water gets deeper, but you are easily able to wade through.

207.description: You are in a corridor running east-west. To the west the corridor is flooded. The water looks very deep.

208.description: You are at an intersection. The corridor leading east is dark and damp. From the south comes a disgusting smell.

209.description: The corridor comes to an end in a locked door. The barred window in it tells yo uthat you have come across a prison of some sorts. You cannot see any prisoners inside, but you never know...

211.description: You are in a corridor running north-south. There is a horrible smell from the south. In the west wall of the corridor is a wooden door.

212.description: You feel bitterly cold here.As you recover from the shock you realise that the way in is blocked.To the west the bright sheen of daylight scours your eyes. Above you,set high into the ceiling is a wooden trapdoor.

213.description: In the east wall of the corridor is a dark opening. The stench is almost overpowering. A few metres south the corridor ends in a door.

214.description: This disgusting place is the rubbish tip. It is full of foul-smelling slime and mouldy, unrecognisable objects.

215.description: You walk south to the end of the corridor and open the door. On the other side is a corridor which runs west and south.

216.description: You are at a bend in the corridor - it runs west and south. In the north wall at the bend is a wooden door.

217.description: You are in a short corridor. From the west you can hear conversation, but do no trecognise the language.

218.description: You are at an entrance to a large, gloomy cavern, which is so big that you cannot see the other side. A dark passage leads off to the east.

219.description: You are in a corridor running north-south. You arrive at an opening in the east wall. Inside you see what must be a large kitchen, where food is prepared for the orcs.

220.description: You are in an east-west corridor. On the south wall, a locked door is marked: '221 Wilson Suite'

221.description: You are in the kitchen. A large table runs down the centre of the room and you can see ovens around the walls. In the south-west corner of the room is an ope n fire. The smoke leaves through a hole in the roof. Half of the east wall is a wooden screen.

222.description: You are behind the wooden screen. This is just an extension of the kitchen. The wooden table is stained red, and there are various small knives about. There is a door in the north wall.

223.description: This room is where the orcs store their food. There is a door in the south wall.

224.description: The wall ends here. You can follow it south, or east and round to the south. Numerous voices can be heard and from somewhere near is coming an agonized groaning.

225.description: You are in a corner. The wall runs north and east.

226.description: You are in the south-east corner of this part of the cavern. The corpse seems to have been partially chewed. In the wall are scratched the words : ' HERE LIES BOV. PLEASE LEAVE HIM ALONE. '

227.description: In this corner is a pile of corpses. The smell is quite strong and rats crawl among the bodies.

228.description: You are near the north wall. Further west along the wall there is a fire

229.description: You are near a fire. There is

230.description: You are high up in the clouds, floating in the air. You are not sure whether this is reality or a dream, but you could probably make a fairly good guess.

231.description: You are on a large cloud which you believe to be shaped like a keyboard. Maybe you should go a bit easy on the old computing.

232.description: You are floating in the air with no visible means of support, and so is something else ...

233.description: The scene gradually changes and you find, not entirely to your surprise, that you are now a short distance from a base on the moon (though whether it is really white, gold and assorted shades of pink you don't know).

234.description: You fall off the moon (a very neat trick!) and hurtle towards the earth. As you fall, you meet a very long-haired hippy who claims to be your inner self.

235.description: You arrive at a green, sunny meadow. You can see oval footprints in the grass, which are evenly spaced, as though things have been marching up and down the field.

236.description: You fall through nothingness very, very fast indeed. You can just see a mist ahead of you.

237.description: You are at the Gates of Delirium. Anyone who can tell MARK the relevance of every room to the east of here, including this one, will get a huge prize (and Imean HUGE!).

238.description: You are in a field full of corn. Strange shapes light up the night.

239.description: You are in a large airship. There is a distinct smell of lemons coming from somewhere.

240.description: You are in a town in the Wild West. A band of men, wanted dead or alive, are running wild in the streets, with their hands raised.

241.description: You are on the Lake Geneva shoreline. A hard-headed woman called Nancy is strangling a soft-hearted man. A blind man is shooting at Frank Zappa and the Mothers.

242.description: You reach an English market stall. One man is selling carefully weighed pieces of earth, another is giving prizes to people who see certain birds, and anothe r is selling mallets.

243.description: You are on a dark planet. Strangely enough, you can see a gibbering idiot on a small stretch of grass, and a rabbit digging a hole. The sun is coming up behi ndyou.

244.description: You go all around the world on a mystery train and arrive on the front line, where you find a family at war with some electric gypsies.

245.description: What is the name of Thor's mighty warhammer?

246.description: This is an empty chamber. Carved from pure crystal but devoid of anything usefu lexcept for a heavy wooden chest lying in the centre of the room.

247.description: You are in an empty room devoid of all objects and description.

249.description: You are at the end of the road. Clues may be had at a price and there is a bell on the wall for this purpose. (First clue - this room has no relevance).

250.description: You are in FROGPOND GATE 1 - VILLAGE OF ARGAND. There is a teleport gate to the north.

251.description: You are in FROGPOND GATE 2 - GOBLIN SCHOOL. There is a teleport gate to the north.

252.description: You are in FROGPOND GATE 4 - CASTLE. There is a teleport gate to the south.

253.description: You are in FROGPOND GATE 3 - ISLAND (NW). There is a teleport gate to the north .

254.description: You are in FROGPOND GATE 5 - TROLLS' DEN. There is a teleport gate to the south .
