256.description: You are in a corridor in Frogpond.

257.description: You are in a corridor in Frogpond. There is a door to the north.

258.description: You are in a corridor in FROGPOND. There is a door to the north.

259.description: You are at the end of a corridor in FROGPOND.

260.description: You are in a corridor. Printed on a locked door on the south wall is: '261 Wilson Suite'

261.description: You are in a spare storeroom. This is fairly well furnished with a small table in the corner.

262.description: You are in a corridor. Printed on the locked door in the south wall is: '263 Churchill Suite'

263.description: rope/Key 613/A Bro You are in a sparsely furnished cave. There is a small table in the corner.

264.description: You are at the eastern end of the corridor. Printed on the locked iron door in the south wall is: '265 Attlee Suite'

265.description: You are in a sparsely furnished room. There are several empty cupboards around the walls, and there is a hole high up on the wall. ULADDER:073

266.description: You are in the gymnasium. You are surprised to find large amounts of blood splattered around the walls and on the wall-bars.

267.description: You are in a side room off the gymnasium. Various badminton nets lie around.

268.description: You are in the prefects' common room. There are pool tables in the middle of th efloor and nude goblin pin-ups on the wall.

269.description: You are in Room 61. This room is relatively tastefully decorated, if you happen to be colour-blind. You can go East down the stairs into the main school, or West into another classroom.

270.description: You are in room 62. The sixth-form currently inhabiting this place are in the process of squashing their unfortunate form-master behind the blackboard.

271.description: You are in room 63. Room 64 (aaaggghhh!!!) is to the east. The blackboard on th esouth wall seems somehow unreal.

272.description: You are in room 64 (and don't you wish you weren't?). There are holes all aroun dthe room, the blackboard is held on at one corner, and the East window is no more.

273.description: You pass through two old rusted iron gates and up a huge winding path. Lightnin gflashes in the distance, producing occasional silhouettes of a dark castle.

274.description: You pass through two huge doors into the main entrance hall of the castle. Gothic architecture is evident. Huge cobwebs hang from the ceiling and many contain dead bats.

275.description: This room is surrounded by huge doors, all of which are open. The room itself i sbare of furniture except for one huge table.

276.description: On a huge table stands an old brass candlestick and two wine goblets. There are two food platters containing bones.

277.description: 'You took your time' says the Hobbit.'Now , what is the first month in the Hobb it year?'

280.description: 'And finally the fourth if you don't mind.'

281.description: The Hobbit beams and shows you an altar with a golden head on top.'Congratulati ons and I hope you solve the quest soon' he says.

282.description: Greetings oh lowly one. This is a recorded message and will not even slightly self destruct. To gain access to the next question answer this one in a single word.What might a basilisk also be known as?

283.description: That was too easy, but lets see you answer this one mortal! The Sphinx in Egypt has the head of which king?

284.description: Damn you!! Take your bauble and be off before I get REALLY angry.

285.description: O.K. You have got yourself well and truely in it this time. To get out of IT fill in the missing words. Gilgalad was an ........ king,

287.description: The last whose realm was fair and ....... ,

289.description: Well done. Your research has paid off and so to the gnome puts a chest on the floor.

290.description: You are in the eidolon's haunt. He does not like visitors so make your buisness sharp and to the point. First , who was the dragon in farmer Giles of Ham (the book that is)

291.description: Which babylonian goddess was a dragon?

292.description: Now what was the name of the great white dragon in the Crystal Shard?

293.description: The snake hisses "On which day did the thrush hit the rock in The Hobbit?"

294.description: And what was the dragon's name?

295.description: You are in a temporal vortex. Multicoloured smoke swirls around you, and no matter which way you move, you seem to approach a light in the distance.

296.description: You are in a temporal vortex. Multicoloured smoke swirls around you, and no matter which why you move, you seem to approach a light in the distance.

297.description: You are in the high priests storeroom.

299.description: You are in hal storeroom but as he has used up virtually every other room that wont surprise you.

300.description: You are in a corridor. There are various bright decorations around the walls an dceiling and a mural shows smiling figures holding axes. There is a jagged cra ckin the north wall, with steam pouring out of it.

301.description: You are in a narrow tunnel. The walls are dripping with slime. Even smaller passages lead north, east and west. A small sign pointing east reads 'This way to the Copyright Message'

302.description: The passage way get narrower and narrower. You can only just turn round.

303.description: You are in narrow twisting tunnel. Every few feet is turns sharply in a different direction.

304.description: You are lost in a twisting tunnel.

305.description: You are lost in a twisting tunnel.

306.description: You are in a slightly wider corridor, though it is still damp and claustrophobi cIt turns a sharp corner to the north, and also leads south.

307.description: You are in a twisting tunnel. A steel shutter blocks the way north, on which is printed ' D.D.P.C. Construction in progress. Sorry for any inconvenience.'

308.description: You are in a small room deep underground. The walls are made from smooth granit eTo the north, steps lead up, to the east there is a trapdoor without a handle (and cannot be opened) and to the west there is a narrow passage.

309.description: You are at a junction. Corridors lead north east and west. A larger board reads 'Argand Village'. No fighting please, all violent adventurers will be fined or imprisoned. Joint council of Dungeon Settlements.' There is a FROGHOP telepor t gate.

310.description: You are walking down the back wall of what seems to be a smithy. You can tell this from the clanking noises and the billows of smoke coming out of the chimn ey

312.description: Ahead of you there is a clearing, and to your side^A there is a dank, musty, da rk,damp, cold, and desolate cave. (Love the adjectives ?)

313.description: You are at the end of the corridor. Dooors lead off in all directions. A u unpleasant smeel comes from the west door.

314.description: You are at a junction. Corridors lead north, east and west.

315.description: You are in a newly constructed corridor. Varnished wooden beams support the roo fans there is a pleasant aroma of pine needles. There is a door in the west wal l and the corridor continues south and north.

316.description: You are in a corridor. There is a door to the east and to the west there is an arch upon which is written in florid lettering : 'ARGAND POLICE'

317.description: You are in a wide corridor in the Argand Village. To the east a smaller corrido rdisappears into gloom. The corridor seems to continue north, but a sign over this exit reads: 'Thankyou for visiting Argand'. There is a door to the west.

318.description: You are in a long stone room . There is a passage to the north which leads to the treasure chambers .

319.description: You are in the ante-hall of the Governor's residence. There are heavy iron door sto the north.

320.description: You are in the Governor's Hall. It is a huge room with marble pillars, and ston eguards sculpted from granite. In the centre of the room is a large wooden desk covered in trailing vines. There is a locked and barred door to the east.

321.description: 30/A small dagge You are in the Governor's Treasury. There is a locked door to the west.

322.description: You are in a small square room with a high ceiling. Strange figures are engrave daround the walls and the large stone statue stares vacantly at you. There is a large door, studded with metal spikes to the south.

323.description: You are in a narrow corridor. You can go east and west.

324.description: You are inside the old police station of Argand. Pictures of wanted criminals, such as Satan, Jodrell, Phoenix, Tokeo, and Conan line the wall. There is a locked cell to the south.

325.description: You are in a prison cell. It is dark, damp and unpleasant. Through the barred and locked door to the north, you can see a police station.

326.description: You are in some sort of meeting area. A large empty ring in the centre of the room is surrounded by seats. Around the edge of the room are flowerbeds, plant edwith strange orchids and fungi. There is a noticeboard on the wall.

327.description: You are in a small grocery. Bags of maize and wheat are stacked up along the walls together with piles of household goods: planks of wood, nails, scissors etc. Dusty adverts for food products hang from the ceiling.

328.description: You are in a blacksmith's shop. There is a heavy anvil and a furnace, and various half finished metal objects lie scattered around the room. It is very hot here. There are doors to the east and west.

329.description: You are in another Argand house. It is dark and smelly and drops of water fall from the high ceiling. On the west wall there is heavy trap door, but you cann otopen it because the handle has been removed.

330.description: You are in a little Argand house. Although there is only one tiny exit, it is quite cheerful and a log fire provides a bright glow. There is little of value here however.

331.description: You are in a small cave. From the contents - a bedstead, table and stove - you assume it is a house, though it is extremely damp and dark. The only exit is through the small door to the east through which you entered.

332.description: You are in a small cave. It is EXTREMELY smelly.

333.description: The dead end has been tunnelled through by an entthusiastic adventurer to revea la new passageway. A sign reads "I know I've been there, and those monsters are hard!!!!". ./

334.description: The dead end has been tunnelled through by an enthusiastic adventurer to reveal a new passageway. A sign reads: "I know, I've been there, and those monsters are hard!!!!". ./

335.description: You are lost in a twisting tunnel.

336.description: You are lost in a twisting tunnel.

337.description: You are on a long staircase which goes down to the south and up to the north. You cannot see the top. Strange figures are drawn in soot on the walls.

338.description: You can see a ROBOT DEMIGOD leering above you. Try your luck at killing him or GET OUT SMARTISH

339.description: You are on a long staircase. You cannot see the bottom. The stairs here have moss growing on them, and there are some dead leaves on the floor.

340.description: You are in a small round room at the top of a flight of stairs. On the north wall a steel ladder leads up through a hatch in the ceiling. Bright daylight pours in and there is a light breeze

341.description: You are on a gravelled path. To the north there is a fence topped with sharp spikes, and there are fields to the south. The path continues east and west.

343.description: You are walking along a wide path. It leads east, west and south. To the south there is an ugly square building with many windows. It is very windy.

344.description: You are in a shrineYou are in the fourth room of the Gerbilcard section.

345.description: You are in a meaty room.Occupied by a body-guard who gets very angry at people entering this place.

346.description: You arrive at a T-junction. To the east the road continues in front of a vast many-windowed building, with a large arch surmounted by a white clock. To the west there is a white pavilion. To the north the road goes between two buildings.

349.description: You are in the Entrance Hall to Frogpond. There is a heavy wooden door to the west. A sign on it reads : "Friends of the Gerbil Society. Bonafide FRoGs use key 349. No insurance salesmen, visitors, Priests or other undesirables."

350.description: Monthly/The Independ You are in the Friends of the Gerbil Common Room. It is full of large leather armchairs, glass coffee tables, ivory ashtrays and dragonskin rugs. A large clock ticks loudly and there are shelves stacked with books on all the walls.

351.description: You are in a large ante-room. There is a desk marked RECEPTION which is completely empty apart from a bell and a Silver Reed electronic typewriter. There is a locked door to the east marked 'GERBIL'. There is a noticeboard he re.

352.description: You are in Gerbil's site office. There is a large desk filled with assorted papers and electronic equipment. An Amstrad PC1512 connected to a laser printe r beeps quietly to itself in one corner.

353.description: You are in a mossy cave. Flowers grow in hanging plantpots and there is a general atmosphere of peace and tranquillity. There is a shrine here on top of a fountain. You can hear faint birdsong from high above.

354.description: You are in a half built bar. Planks and mortar and bags of sand are scattered around. To the west a sign over a door reads 'MONTY PYTHON FAN CLUB'. The east corridor has collapsed out of boredom.

355.description: You are in a half built bar. Planks and mortar and bags of sand are scattered around. To the west a sign over a door reads 'MONTY PYTHON FAN CLUB'. The east corridor has collapsed out of boredom.

356.description: You are in a small, featureless concrete cell with no doors, windows or other exits. It is empty apart from a wooden stool and an empty jug. Chalked on the wall is: 'TOADSTOOL IV'

357.description: You are in a small, featureless concrete cell with no doors, windows or other exits. It is empty apart from a wooden stool and an empty jug. Chalked on the wall is: 'TOADSTOOL IV'

359.description: This is FERRARI's workshop. A few bits and bobs lie scattered around in neat an dtidy fashion. A superb prototype anti gravity machine is suspended from the ceiling above a temple of turbos and tyres.

361.description: You enter this room down a long flight of steps. It is dark and warm, and fires burn in various alcoves in the walls. At the top of the north staircase, a hea vywooden door has been smashed by some sort of blunt weapon.

362.description: You are in a ruined temple. It is full of broken firewood of straw, most of which is badly charred. There is an exit to the north, but it is blocked by piles of sawdust and twigs.

363.description: You are in a rather grubby and disreputable shryne, the sort which belongs to Gods who smash in your windows if you are an atheist. Brocades hang half-heartedly from the walls, completely hiding a small wheel.

365.description: As you walk along this passage, it changes from a damp tunnel into a wide, square corridor. Finally you come to a door. Strange glowing gases float throu ghit and you can hear loud manic laughter.

366.description: You are in the Temple of Greed. Flashing neon lights decorate the walls and strange chemicals bang and sparkle in goldfish bowls. In the centre of the toom is a huge, ornate lever covered in silver filigree.

367.description: You are in a small, dark side room. From the west you can hear muffled bangs and manic shouting.

368.description: You appear to have fallen into a large smelly pit. There is a trapdoor high above you and there is soggy and steaming straw all over the floor. There is a n exit to the south.

369.description: You are in a high earth tunnel lit by candles in iron brackets. There are steps up to the east.

370.description: You are in a small cave. A very narrow passageway leads east, and there is an open gate to the west. A sign above it reads 'YOU WILL DIE IF YOU GO THROUGH HERE.'

371.description: You are in a tunnel. It runs east-west.

372.description: You are walking along a wide north-south tiled corridor. A heavy iron pipe comes out from the floor half way along and disappears through the ceiling. There is a jagged hole in the pipe through which a stream of liquid pours.

374.description: As you walk along the corridor, it becomes mistier and mistier until you find yourself walking through a dense fog. You can just make out a faint light to the north.

375.description: You are walking through a green fog which thins out to the north. To your surprise you hear a voice say quietly 'Warning, psychedelic selection procedur e commencing.'

376.description: You are in a large square room with silvery flat walls. Hundreds of rubber ball sare bouncing around at high speed off the walls, ceiling and floor. There are doors to the west and east.

380.description: You are in a dingy corridor. The air is thick with the choking smell of incense .There is a door to the south, but an iron gate, which is padlocked, blocks the way forward.

381.description: You are in a corridor. There is a locked gate to the south, but to the north you see a strange green blinding light.

385.description: Suddenly the ground slips away beneath you and you slide forward at great speed into a deep, murky pool at the end of the path. You notice several large black shapes darting towards you. The east bank looks solid but is out of your reac h.

402.description: You are at a junction. A large board hangs on the wall and has some writing on it. Two large tunnels lead off, to the north and south. ^B

403.description: fas You are in the guard troll's living quarters. The room is barely furnished, bu tseems comfortable enough. There are two chairs, and a table which has been se t for dinner. A bright fire burns in the corner.

404.description: You are in the north passageway. The ceiling is high overhead, and a cold wind whispers past you towards the north. The floor is smooth underfoot.

405.description: You are in the large corridor running north-south. The walls are smooth and glisten in the light of a torch in a wall bracket. To the south you can see a guard post.

406.description: This corridor runs south and east. A chill wind blows east, and the walls are rough.

407.description: You are at what seems to be the entrance to a house. A small oak door blocks your way to the east. A sign on the wall says 'SNUFFLE'S RESIDENCE - KEEP OUT '

408.description: You are in the living room. Over the fireplace there is a shelf, on which rest the portraits of some extremely nasty looking young trolls. The walls are tastelessly decorated with amateur pictures.

409.description: You are in the corridor. A sign on the wall says 'GARDS MES THRU ERE' and an arrow beside it points south. On the wall someone has scrawled 'Aren't you fe d up of bad spellings by now?'

410.description: 1 You are in an older part of the lair. The tunnel seems natural, and a diffuse red light seems to come from the south tunnel. A warm wind blows west.

411.description: You are in a small alcove in the passageway. A soothing gold radience seems to emanate from a niche in the wall, over which there is an inscription which you cannot read. In the niche is a small shrine.

412.description: You are at a dead end. The trolls must never come here, because there are clea rsigns of occupation by a member of another race. The place is a complete tip.

413.description: You are at a dead end. The trolls must never come here, because there are clea rsigns of occupation by a member of another race. The place is a complete tip.

415.description: A leathe You are at the west side of the volcano. The lava boils below, and someone has scrawled 'BEWARE THE D..G.N' on the wall. The message is half obliterated by scorch marks.

416.description: A small You are in a very large cave. The walls are scorched, and a large sign says 'SMAUG EAT YOUR HEART OUT'. There are bones and gobbets of flesh scattered about.

417.description: You find yourself in a small forest full of greenery and foliage. There are som estrange looking trees about, which reach high into the sky.

418.description: You are in the south-east corner. Above your head, you can see that someone ha scarved a cheery baboon-like face into the rock, and the ruddy glow from the la valights up his cheeks in mirth.

419.description: You are on a narrow ledge, and you can just make out a faint glow from the sout h

420.description: At this point, the ledge approaches the spire most closely, but is still too fa rto jump. Tantalizing shadows dance on the spire, but you cannot see them clearly.

421.description: You walk into a large hall with a boiling yellow river running through it. Sulphurous fumes rise up into a small chimney in the roof, which is being rebuilt by some weary trolls.

422.description: dagge You are on the spire in the centre of the volcano. The heat is immense, and th eground shimmers before your gaze. The lava below bubbles, and you seem to see the figures of souls in torment.

423.description: You are on the spire in the centre of the volcano. The heat is immense, and th eground shimmers before your gaze. The lava below bubbles, and you seem to see the figures of souls in torment.

424.description: The corridor begins to turn south. There is a small hole in the north wall. Yo ucan probably just squeeze through it, but it looks dark and uninviting.

425.description: You are in an Oaken room Next to you is an open door.Unfortunately people Are w atching the Entrance.

426.description: You are in a room surrounded by golden objects.Many Odd People Surround the wal ls looking at you.

427.description: You are at the end of a corridor. The wall in front of you looks suspiciously blank, but you can see no obvious way of getting through.

428.description: You are at the end of a corridor. The wall in front of you looks suspiciously blank, but you can see no obvious way of getting through.

429.description: Here the corridor bends north. The rock on the north wall seems fused, as though by some great heat, and the walls are rounded and smooth.

430.description: You are in one of the most astoundingly boring corridors in the whole Adventure e.You really wouldn't believe how boring this place is. Really amazingly borin g is the impression I'm trying to get across here.

431.description: You are in the guards mess, and it is. Empty flagons litter the tables, and th ebeer from them lies in puddles on the floor. A pair of dice lie on one of the tables, next to a pack of cards.

432.description: A satchel of gol This corridor begins to bend round to the south. A sign saying 'STOREROOM' points north.

433.description: You are in somebody's study. A massive wooden desk is in the centre of the roo mand is covered with papers. The floor has a dark green carpet which is staine d with red in places.

434.description: You are in a storeroom. As usual, it is filled with useless junk. Cobwebs cover the walls, and the whole room looks fairly decrepit and unused.

435.description: You are in a dark and gloomy hole, the walls of which are covered with thick cobwebs. There are some bones and gobbets of flesh scattered about.

436.description: You are perched perilously on a narrow ledge. A passage leads back into the mountainside, and a sheer rock face looms above you. The wind blows wildly, threatening to blow you off.

437.description: The ledge widens here slightly and your footing is a little more sure. Below th eledge you can see a green and pleasant valley. The ledge continues further on tothe south.

438.description: Here the ledge narrows and turns back into the mountainside. A dark cave lies in an outfold of rock to the south. You can see the glimmerings of a fire inside it.

440.description: You are in a small, disused crack. Dust coats the floor, and cobwebs cling to the walls. There are the outlines to a door in the wall behind the grime.

441.description: You are in a forgotten treasure room, with faded wall hangings portraying battl escenes. The dust is thick, but has been disturbed near a door to the east.

442.description: A golden treasure chest~300 You are in a small room next to the forgotten treasury. There is dim light fro ma slit in the wall. There is a noisome smell in the air, and slime on the floor.

443.description: You are in a very large cave indeed. The walls tower above you, and there is a large hole in the roof. There are bones and gobbets of flesh on the floor, an d a sign on the wall says 'SMAUG EAT YOUR HEART OUT'. ^B

444.description: 3/The ace of s You are in an ornate office, with a large noticeboard on one wall.A large selection of records stands by an impressive hi-fi, which is running.

445.description: You are stuck in a room with no exits. Blood covers the walls, and ghosts flit around the place providing dim illumination. ./

449.description: You are floating on a cloud, somewhere above the dungeon. A glowing portal lead sthe way to the north.

450.description: You enter a surprisingly brightly lit room. A sign on the south wall reads 'ZOO - Admission free. Party bookings are safer. Life insurance only paid if collected in person.'

453.description: You are outside another cage. A notice on the wall reads 'Please do not feed th eanimals.'

454.description: The bars of this cage are badly singed, and so are all the corpses.

455.description: 3 The bars of this cage are badly bent. To the east, the corridor widens again. ./

456.description: All roads lead to Rome. All roads in the Zoo lead to here. Eventually. Of cours ethis wasn't the original description, but what is these days ?

457.description: You arrive at a cage. There are an alarming number of corpses in the cage (though it is comforting to find none outside), but surprisingly there is very little blood.

458.description: This cage is obviously for smaller animals, as the bars are closer together.

459.description: This cage is made of glass to stop anything getting through it.

460.description: This cage is made of glass. The wall on the other side of the cage is covered i nscorch marks.

461.description: You are in the head zookeeper's office. There are papers scattered around all over the place, and pictures of wierd and wonderful animals decorate the walls . There is a large, grandly decorated door in the north wall.

462.description: You are in a large, well lit room. The locked door on the north wall is marked 'SHARLOC'S OFFICE - NO ADMISSION'. There is a noticeboard on the east wall.

463.description: You are in the office of Sharloc. An Amstrad computer is furiously working away in one corner. The screen reads 'Gauntlet loaded, press any key to play'.

464.description: You are in MARK's storage room, but he won't be needing it any more, so you needn't fret about it.

465.description: In this room, the ancient tea lady goes about her buisiness of placing food in this common room, once MARK the Corrupt's, and no the head zoo keeper's.

466.description: Somewhere round here, were exits into the underground, and the maze. They seem to have been blasted in to nothingness by some contraption called NEWADV.

467.description: You are in the maze. There is a locked door in the north wall.

473.description: You are in the maze. There is a draught coming from under the locked door in th eeast wall.

474.description: You are in a long tunnel. There is a very strong breeze coming from round the corner.

478.description: You are in the maze. A sign above a door in the north wall reads 'GIVE YE UP? THEN COME YE THROUGH YE DOOR OF COWARDS.'

484.description: You are in the maze. There is a locked door in the north wall. Written on it is 'PUT YE KEY IN YE LOCK FOR YE TREASURE.'

485.description: You are in a large room. The walls are well decorated, and a stream of clear, fresh water runs from a hole in the wall. A sign above the arch in the north wall reads 'WELL DONE! HAVE YE WELL-EARNED REST.'

488.description: You are in a corridor. Do you need asgard?

489.description: You reach an iron gate which opens out onto a schoolyard. You stop to read the sign on the gate. It says 'Ver Gobberlin Skuwel iz owpun aftur ver ollydais.'

490.description: You walk down the playground. From the barbed wire around the walls you guess that a fair amount of absconding goes on (especially through the FROGHOP teleport gate).

491.description: You enter the playground of the goblin's school. The playground continues North and South, and the entrance to the school building is West.

492.description: You are at the far end of the goblin playground.

493.description: You are in the cloakroom. You can go North into Room 1, South into Room 2, East into the playground or West up the stairs into the sixth-form area.

494.description: You enter a classroom in an even worse state of disrepair than your form room.

495.description: When you enter this classroom, you realise that you have disrupted a biology class : frogs are leaping about on the desks and performing other unsavoury activities about which you would not wish to hear.

496.description: You enter Room 3, a classroom which appears to be almost tidy, if a little disorganised.

497.description: You enter Room 4. You have interrupted a rather important class - the fifth for mare being told about their GFJKRSGCSE's.

498.description: You are in Room 5. Compared to this, the rest of the school is a dead zone - yo uhave to duck regularly to dodge anything from ink pellets to flying chairs.

499.description: You enter Room 6. From the high pitched screams, you guess that you must have intruded on a first form.

500.description: You are in a passage which rises to the east. The floor is covered in bones and there is a rotting corpse with a look of agony on his face. Through the cobwebs you can see light from above. ./

501.description: You are at the end of a passage. There used to be a locked grating above, but some adventurer with a boltcutter has removed the padlock. You can see dayligh t at last.

502.description: You are standing by the grating. From down below you here the echos of a thousand lost souls. In the distance you can see a magnificent castle, a lake with an island, and a mountain with a great spire.

504.description: You are in what appears to be a makeshift prison. Scratchings on the walls indicate many people have done time in here, and the smell is abominable.

505.description: You are on the path. There is a brick building to the south, and the path continues east and west.

506.description: You are inside the brick building. Now you know why you were hearing screams; this is the torturer's chamber. Ugly instruments whose uses you can't imagine hang from the walls.

507.description: You are on the path. There is an old building to the south.

508.description: You are inside an old building. Rotted carcasses and foul-smelling fungus line the walls. The window has been smashed by a brick.

509.description: You are in the main quadrangle of the old complex. There is a bricked up exit t othe north, stables to the east, a path to the west and a path to the south.

510.description: You are in the stables. The stalls are broken and falling down, and the place is in general a tip. There is a hayloft above, but you would need a ladder to reach it.

511.description: You are in the store room of the stables. The remains of leather saddles and whips hang from the walls, and there are a couple of bales of hay in the corne r.

512.description: You are in the hay loft. You have a scenic view through the winch hatch, but you suspect most people who have been here haven't been too interested in looking out the window.

513.description: The path leads southwards towards what seems to be a large mist-enshrouded castle of some sort. Mists hide the surrounding area from prying eyes. A rotte d signpost lies fallen and un-noticed here.

514.description: You are walking on a path through the old gardens. The flowers need some looking after (apply to a Demigod for a holiday job) and the privvy bush has long since had it.

515.description: You are on a path amongst the privvy bushes. A sign reads "NO BALL GAMES".

516.description: You are at the end of the garden path. A gardener is here trimming the privy bushes. A wheelbarrow full of clippings rests here.

518.description: o You are standing by the castle portcullis. A sign says "SOD OFF", and you can tell from the scratch marks and the flesh hanging off the portcullis that it closes fairly often. ./

519.description: You are under the main arch. To the north there is a portcullis, and south take syou into the castle. Above, a brightly painted boss in the roof carries the initials "DPS".

520.description: You have probably just been under the main arch of the castle entrance. So now you are probably in a porters lodge, but if you dissagree strongly tell me!!!

521.description: On second thaughts this might be the guard house, since e^Aast looks interestin g, if you dissagree strongly then write your name on a postcard addressed to Os ty and then throw the post card into a large incinerator. Happy adventuring Os ty!!

522.description: You are in the guard house. There are four bunkbeds, a table, and a simple stov ein the corner. If you pinch their baked beans they might get mighty angry. There is a note pinned on a noticeboard which says "DON'T FORGET THE HOVIS EX TRATHICK".

523.description: You are in the main castle courtyard. High stone walls surround you, and various passageways lead off.

524.description: You are in the music room. A pianola is bashing out Bach's Klavierubung in E Minor (maybe you recognise it) and there are other cylinders and bits of sheet music lying about.

525.description: This is an annex to the music room. There are piles of paper strewn accross the floor, the ashtrays are full, and their is an empty bottle of 'Teachers' whisk y on the table.

526.description: You are in the treasury. There is a heavy wooden table in the centre of the room (presumably for counting coins on) and leather pouches are strewn all ove r the floor.

527.description: You are in the bank. There is a locked high security door in the east wall, and you can feel heat coming from the north. A pretty cashier smiles at you from behind a desk. There is a bell here.

528.description: You are in the Treasure Vault of the Castle. A large hunky guard stands silent here watching you carefully. Masses and masses of accumulated wealth are heape d in piles.

529.description: You are in the smelting room. Here, pure gold and silver ingots are melted down and coins are made. A sign says "BRINKS MAT WELCOMES YOU".

530.description: You are in the main passage. The stuffed heads of various wild beasts adorn the walls and glare at you with piercing eyes, trying to tell you something throug h the silence. ./

531.description: You are in the main passage. The stuffed heads of various wild beasts adorn the walls and glare at you with piercing eyes, trying to tell you something throug h the silence.

532.description: You are, I think, in the main passage; which is odd...no it isn't...sorry wrong page. Oh dear well I suppose it is my own fault, I shoul not have gone into Sputnik's office...well well. Anyone got any aspirin?

533.description: You are in the ballroom, beautifully decored in the style of Michelangelo. The floorboards are a bit suspect in places, so if the mood takes you, don't do the Elephant Dance.

534.description: You are standing by some ornate French windows. Outside are some gardens, and in the distance you can see a forest below a mountain. There is also a lake wi than island at the centre.

535.description: These grounds have now been opened, but I'd be careful out there.

536.description: You are in the servant's Common Room. You can tell the kind of people they are by the comics on the coffee table. A poster on the wall describes how to survi vein the castle: "DON'T BOTHER".

537.description: orged iron sh You are in the never ending passage. The wood panelling is now as holy as the Pope due to wood termites. ./

539.description: You are in the castle's Frozen Food department which is not yet open, due to a few malfunctions in the canning processes.. Packs of partly frozen goods lie a llover the floor. A steel door misted over with icicles provides access from th e west.

540.description: You are in the ancient weapons shop. Some of these things look really mean. Unfortunately, there are people about who know how to use them.

541.description: You are in the dojo. Those who do not bow before standing on the mat will be executed immediately. A sign reads: "FIGHT THE NINJA FOR GLORY AND A FEW XP".

542.description: You are in the oriental room. Valuable neo-Corinthian paintings adorn the walls ,and a poster in Chinese says "IT IS NOT MAN THAT MAKES TRUTH GREAT, BUT TRUTH THAT MAKES MAN GREAT". You hear chopping sounds from the west.

547.description: 3 You are in the Hall of Spirits. Screams echo around and around and the swirling mists of time obscure your vision. There is an orange glow from the south.

548.description: You are walking down the main passageway. South is an amazing doorway, north yo ucan see a long passageway with light at the end of it. Rooms also lead off eas t and west.

549.description: You are in the Alchemist's Laboratory. I think he's been experimenting with sugar lumps, since he won't come down from the ceiling. However, there are som e useful chemicals here if you like drinking meths.

550.description: You are in an annex to the Alcemist's laboratory. A very peculiar creature is/was here.

551.description: You are in the Red Room.

552.description: You are in the Orange Room.

553.description: You are in the Yellow Room.

554.description: You are in the Green Room.

555.description: You are in the Blue Room.

556.description: You are in the Indigo Room.

557.description: You are in the Violet Room at the end of the Rainbow. Your way south is blocked by a deep and wide pit, but there are rafters overhead you might be able to swing on.

558.description: he krill o You are in the exit room. A sign reads: "HOPE YOU ENJOYED YOUR TRIP, MAN". Ther eis a magic door in the south wall, and the way north is blocked by a deep pit. However, those rafters are still there!!!!

559.description: You are in the throne room of the Master of the castle. He would welcome your prescence,but at the moment he's gone to the chippy.A gold slot is inset in the wall.

561.description: You are in the dark caves of the catacombs.

576.description: You are in the crypt at the end of the catacombs. There is a locked door in the east wall, and a few open coffins are lying about. A bright light seeps round the edge of the locked door.

577.description: You are in the exit room. There is a magic door in the east wall, and a door in the west wall leads back to the crypt. The room is lit by a beautiful ball of floating light.

578.description: You are walking through the everglades. Leaves crunch underfoot and birds twitter in the branches high above. In the distance you can see a spire on top of a mountain.

579.description: You are in a small alcove outside the Trolls' Holiday Home. A delightful fire i sburning in the middle of the clearing. Wierd and wonderful music dances its wa y to you from the east.

580.description: nk/A small bear-ski You are in the trolls' holiday home. There are a couple of fishing rods in the corner and the odd cracked jam jar lies on the floor. This room has a small fi reburning in the centre of the room. A certificate reads: "12 YEARS SERVICE TO THE GREAT MAGE".

581.description: You are in the clearing. There is a chopping block here, and a pile of wooden staves is stacked against the wall of the hut. You can also see a hollow tree and hear the sound of wood nymphs singing.

582.description: You are walking through the petrified forest. Watch you don't trip up, since the leaves on the floor here are not as soft as you might like. To the north- east you can see the glinting of a large expanse of water.

583.description: You are at a T-junction in the path through the forest. To the north there is a lake, and the path rises to the west as it enters rocky terrain.

584.description: You are standing by the lakeshore. In the middle of the lake there is an island ,but you couldn't swim that far. There is a boat quay, but at the moment it is empty and there is only an old oily rope tied to it.

585.description: You are in the rocky canyon, banked by trees on either side. There are distant wailing sounds, and a heavily dismembered corpse lies on the ground. Whatever killed the corpse must have had some set of teeth.

586.description: You are walking along the canyon, which rises to the east. The great tower is clearly visible now in its full glory splendour. A sign reads 'BEWARE THE MAGE NARGOTHRON IN THE ICE TOWER'.

587.description: You are standing in a narrow fissure which leads underneath the mountain. The walls are covered with a thin film of soot, and you can hear great roaring sounds from within the bowels of the cave system.

588.description: You are in a vast cave. Exits lead off in all directions, and many footprints are pressed into the bat droppings on the floor. However, there is a faint sme llof burning coming from the east, and a mysterious orange weir light hangs overhead.

589.description: You are in the dragon's lair. Ever since her baby gold dragon was locked away in a zoo, she has been extremely swift with anybody bothering her. A sign with charred edges reads: "PLEASE LEAVE ME ALONE". ./

590.description: You are in the dragon's antechamber. A green weir light flits around, revealing many interesting objects in the corners of the cave. However, there is nothing of real value to human beings, but then what adventurers are?

591.description: You are in the Iron Passages. Shielded from the earth's magnetic field, your compass bearings no longer make any sense. UCAGE:612

592.description: You are in the Iron Passages.

593.description: You are in the Iron Passages.

594.description: You are in the Iron Passages.

595.description: You are at a dead end in the Iron Passages. There is a door and a sign which reads: "WORKMAN UNCLE'S ROOM - NO ENTRY".

596.description: You are in Uncle's room. There is an armchair, a TV set and a copy of the Racing Post. A row of shelves holds such necessities as a bottle of Vim (very good for bloodstains) and a box of keys of all shapes and sizes.

598.description: You are in the pirate's hideout. If you've ever been robbed, it's quite likely that your stuff will end up in here. There are chests of treasure, but you don 'thave the Chubb high security keys that are needed.

599.description: You are in the Sorcerer's chamber. There are many books of spells written in th eRune Language of Olde, and a rickety staff stands in the corner. There are a f ewbottles of potions and various other fuming and bubbling liquids.

600.description: You are in a small recess in a cliff. A rope provides a means of exit by climbing to the north.

601.description: You are at the summit of the island. There is a fine view of the lake all around . In the eastern distance you can make out a magificent tower. Just to the south is a shining blue teleport gate.

602.description: You are on a lovely sandy beach. A path rises steeply to the north. To the sout hyou can see a beach across the lake.

603.description: You are standing on top a steep climb. To the south is a beautiful sandy beach, and a cliff path leads east and west.

604.description: You are on a cliff path on the south side of the island. There is a great view. A large notice says "Take a refreshing holiday in a magical land. Just find a boat and use it on the southern beach. Have a nice day!"

605.description: r You are on some high ground next to a small peninsula. A cliff path leads north and south.

606.description: You are on a granite mine. Sharp granite lies spread everywhere.

607.description: You are on a very queer rock. A sign says 'To leave the Island, find a boat and use it on the southern beach.

608.description: You are in a nice sheltered bay. Waves lick the pebbles around you, and in the sand something has marked the words "Hope u like iland. Droor an ure ded." To the south a path rises steeply."

609.description: The northern edge of the island is a few metres to the north. The island's summit lies to south, and a path leads east and west.

610.description: You are situated at the north east corner of the island. Cliffs surround you on most sides, but a thin rope dangles to the south and to the east a thin rope bridge crosses the water to a cave high in a cliff.

611.description: The cliff path stops here, due to violent erosion of the eastof the island. Looking north you can see a small rope two hundred yards away dangling over a cliff.

612.description: You are in the shrine. East back to Iron Passages, south to Crude Arch, west to under Main Arch, north to exit. ^B/

613.description: You are in a dingy alcove.There is a barred door to the south.

614.description: This exit has now been fully closed down by Peter so don't mess it about.

615.description: You are at Highbury and Islington on the G.N. Electrics line. West for the Victoria line.

617.description: You are at Old Street on the G.N. Electrics line. West for the Northern line.

618.description: You are at Moorgate on the Metropolitan line. South for the Circle line.

619.description: You are at Moorgate on the Circle line. North for the Metropolitan line. South for the Northern line.

620.description: You are at Moorgate on the Northern line. West for the Circle line. East for th eG.N. Electrics line.

621.description: ^BYou are at Moorgate on the G.N. Electrics line. West for the Northern line.

622.description: You are at Bank on the Central line. North for the Northern line. South for the Waterloo and City line.

623.description: You are at Bank on the Northern line. West for the Central line.

624.description: You are at Bank on the Waterloo and City line. North for the Central line. East for the escalator link.

625.description: You are at Bank on the escalator link. West for the Waterloo and City line.

626.description: You are at Monument on the escalator link. South for the Circle line.

627.description: You are at Monument on the Circle line. North for the escalator link. South for the District line.

628.description: You are at Monument on the District line. North for the Circle line.

629.description: You are at Liverpool Street on the Circle line. West for the Central line. East for the Metropolitan line.

630.description: You are at Liverpool Street on the Metropolitan line. West for the Circle line.

631.description: You are at Liverpool Street on the Central line. North for the Circle line.

632.description: You are at Aldgate East on the Metropolitan line. South for the District line.

633.description: You are at Aldgate East on the District line. North for the Metropolitan line.

634.description: You are at Whitechapel on the Metropolitan line. South for the District line.

635.description: You are at Whitechapel on the District line. North for the Metropolitan line.

636.description: You are at Woodford on the Central line.

637.description: You are at Mile End on the Central line. South for the District line.

638.description: You are at Mile End on the District line. North for the Central line.

639.description: You are at Barking on the District line.

640.description: You are walking along a cool, dark corridor. The hum of air conditioning is just audible. Suddenly a bright red neon sign lights up: ^W'AND NOW FOR SOMETHING COMPLETELY DIFFERENT.............'

641.description: You are in a large room. The walls of covered with strips of canvas, and there is a gaudy arch to the east. An enormous sign proclaims: 'MONTY PYTHON'S FLYING CIRCUS!!!!!'

642.description: You are in the Ministry for Silly Walks. There is a large desk covered with spilt coffee and smashed cups. A poster on the wall reads: 'The Ministry of Silly Walks needs your support. Grants are available for particularly silly walks.'

643.description: You are in a barber's shop. There is a basin full of blood, and razors and knives of various sorts are strewn over the floor. All the entries on the price list have been crossed out except 'Hair combing - 35p'. The east door leads outside.

644.description: You are in a thick forest. To the south there is a door which appears to lead underground. Several tall pines have been recently chopped down, and a river rushes past not far away.

645.description: You are in a cheese shop, although it does not seem to have any cheese on display (except some runny Camembert which a cat is eating). Loud bazooki musi c is playing in the background. To the east, a locked door is marked 'WORK IN PROGRESS'

646.description: You walk into the back of a large auditorium. On the stage, a man in talking very in Latin. A banner across the back of the hall announces: 'SUMMARISE PROUST IN HIS ENTIRETY IN 15 SECONDS COMPETITION, 1987'

647.description: You are in a pet shop. Various sickly looking dogs, cats, hamsters (and gerbils no doubt) stare indifferently at you. There is a bookcase full of 'TEACH YOURSELF TAXIDERMY' books.

648.description: You are in a small, round cave. To the north an escalator leading down hums quietly to itself.

649.description: You are descending a long escalator.

650.description: You are in a corridor. To the south is the escalator you have just descended. The whirr of air conditioning is audible in the distance.

651.description: You are in a round room. There is an iron gate to the west. A large red sign reads : 'LINK AREA G. DDPC non-recommended zone. Not under jurisdiction of JOI NTCOUNCIL OF DUNGEON SETTLERS. CDB medical insurance NOT valid beyond this poin t.'

652.description: You are in a wide, newly dug tunnel. Halfway along, a sign reads: 'WARNING. The Management cannot be held responsible for the injury or death ofand person passing this point. You are now entering LINK AREA G.'

653.description: There is a vast explosion inside your head - you feel your body being turned inside out - then you are falling from a great height. Suddenly you hit the ground very hard. You are in a red cave. It is extremely hot.

654.description: You are in a narrow corridor which twists round the corner to the east. A cool breeze blows from the south but the walls of the corridor are glowing red in front of you. An old man is standing next to you.

655.description: You are outside what looks like a reception. On the wall is a bell marked RING FOR ATTENTION. Another notice on the wall says 'AUTHORISED PERSONNEL ONLY - PLEASE PRESENT TICKET'

656.description: You are in a very hot room with shelves lining the walls. To the east is a larg efurnace-room and this appears to be where the heat is coming from. On the shelves are various metal objects.

657.description: You are in the furnace-room. In the centre of the room is a large furnace, glowing red from all the heat. There are exits to the south and west.

658.description: You are in a hot, sulphurous tunnel, with a sheer drop at the end. This gap in the game map is breached by a small rope ladder.

659.description: You are at a junction from which four dull red tunnels lead in all directions. You can hear the faint sound of manic laughter and screams from a long way off .

660.description: As you follow the path a scalding white mist billows down from high above, and soon you are completely lost.

661.description: You are in a circular muddy room. There are large three-clawed footprints leading north and south, and there are peculiar stone protuberances in the mud . Occasionally a blast of hot air blows from one of the tunnels to the north an d south.

662.description: You are in a Salamander lair. It is so hot in here that the walls seem to be glowing red, and the strange frescoes which decorate the walls seem to move and shimmer in the heat. There is a heavy lead lever here.

663.description: You are in the lair of the Salamander. This room has seventeen sides and intricate designs have been etched in gold on all of them.

664.description: You are in a large office. Although it seems quite normal apart from the oppressive heat, every time you look closely at something, it fades slowly away. There are huge oval doors to the east and west.

665.description: You are in a large office. Although it seems quite normal apart from the oppressive heat, every time you look closely at something, it fades slowly away. There are huge oval doors to the east and west.

667.description: You are in a square stone room with glowing walls. In the centre of the floor i sa blazing fireplace and large black cinders float slowly in the hot air curren tsA stone bench runs around the walls.

668.description: You are walking along a wide path. Strange, stunted trees grow out of the rock and scalding drops of water fall intermittently from the ceiling. There is an arch to the south marked 'ADMISSIONS' in glowing blue light.

669.description: You are in a large office. There is a desk here, with a typewriter and a telephone. A placard on it reads 'Admissions Demon'. There is a noticeboard wi thseveral memos etc. pinned to it.

670.description: The path comes to a huge gate built from bones. Human skulls decorate the top o fthe spiked railings and a glowing sign announces in blood: THE FIRST GATE OF HELL!

671.description: You are at a crossroads. The east-west corridor seems to be the main route, and there are many footprints, clawprints and tentacleprints in the soft, hot floo r.Sinister passageways wind north and south. It is very, very, very hot.

675.description: You are in a narrow corridor. It is almost pitch black, you cannot seem to ligh ta torch, and the only illumination is the faint glow from the south.

676.description: You are in a small, well lit room which seems to contain an air of evil. A sign overhead swings in the still air and is marked 'Dracular's playpen.' A steep shute, down which you have recently decended, is in the south wall.

678.description: You are in a small room, around the walls of which banks of loudspeakers are radiating heavy metal music at 180 decibels. A few disco lights flash in time with the noise.

679.description: You are in a small round passage which curves to the North and East.A small sig nsays 'Exit to the North'

681.description: This is one of the guest rooms of the Severed Arms Pub.

683.description: You are in a badly vandalised room. All the furniture is charred and smashed, and 'FROGSQUOD STRIKES AGAIN' has been sprayed with an aerosol on one wall.

687.description: You are inside guest room 686.It is unoccupied at the moment.

688.description: A high wood ceiling above your head contains a hologram projection mechanism. A notice in mid air says 'KEY 688 TO EXIT OR INSERT EXIT PASS'. A passage with a locked door lies north.

689.description: bilcard/A long spira You are standing by the exit - it is a whirling blue and yellow timewarp to the north. To the south lies a narrow passage, while a passage leads off to the west.

690.description: What is 9 * 6 - speak the answer to enter! You are at the top of a flight of steps in the inn. Type 'read notice' to see who is staying here.

691.description: You are in the Travellers Rest. This is a large room, suitable for a party of visitors. To the north is the main section of the pub.

693.description: You have a splitting headache, and are very thirsty. Maybe you should not have taken that drink. You are on a couch on the floor of a small room, and a notice on the wall says 'Hangover Recovery". There is a small door to the north. ./

694.description: You are in a small room, which is obviously the inkeeper's living quarters. A door to the west is marked with strange symbols, while a blue sheet of light shimmers in the north wall. A small sign by it says "Porter's lodge".

695.description: You are in a small room which is probably a shrine, judging by the symbols on i ts walls. Many old books are scaterred around, and an old map of the adventure is attatched to one wall.

696.description: You are in the pub. There is a bell on the long reception desk. The Yorkshir e Barman is about to take your order.A Darts board hangs on the wall.

697.description: You are in a dark dimly lit mossy cave.

698.description: You are on a long narrow flight of stairs which descends to below the level of the lake. At the top of the stairs is a locked iron door. A notice says "Congratulations - I bet you drink carling black label"

701.description: You are in the middle of a desert. To the north, you can see more grass than to the south. The grass becomes longer in this area. To the north, you can see th e tops of some tents.

702.description: You are in the middle of a desert. To the north, you can see more grass than to the south. The grass becomes longer in this area. To the north, you can see th e tops of some tents.

703.description: You are in an area to the west of the desert. Here, the desert gives way to a fairly rocky area. To the west is a wide canyon with high, steep sides. The sa ndfeels fairly wet here.

704.description: You are standing in the middle of two high sand dunes. In this area, the short grass is greener than other areas, showing the heavier rainfall recently. To t henorth you can see the tops of some tents.

706.description: You are in the southern regions of the desert. To the north-west you can see a rocky expanse sticking up from the desert. To the south you think you can see anoasis with palm trees.

707.description: You are in the barren desert. The sand is very hot to the touch and to the west you can see an area of rocks. Far in the distance to the north you can see som e mountains. ./

708.description: You are at the foot of a large outcrop of rock. The rocks are a orange-brown colour and to the north, there are some well worn steps up the rock to the top . You can see a small opening in the side of the rockface.

709.description: The ground is hard rock broken only by the well-worn steps cut into the side of the rock-face. A plateau rises up to the west and the steps lead down to the south. Not a lot grows here. ./

710.description: You are at the top of a rocky outcrop in the middle of a desert. The rock here is a darker colour than further down the rock. In the rock, someone has carved 'BEWARE OF THE OLD HERMIT'

711.description: You are inside a very dark cave. Sand has accumulated all over the floor in her efrom years of the wind blowing. You can see daylight to the east but to the we stit is very dark. ./

712.description: You are at the end of a dark cave. There are bones of adventurers lying around on the floor here. To the north, you can see a shimmering yellow hole in the rocks. The sunlight only just reaches in here from the east.

713.description: You are standing in the middle of the village. To the west is a tent with the front flap open. People are bustling about here because this seems to be the central area in the village. In the distance to the south you can see a rocky area.

714.description: You are standing inside a particularily draughty tent. However you can't feel these as your every thought is attuned to the big chauldron with a head bublin g about in it.

715.description: You are in the middle of the village. To the east you can see a tent much large rthan the rest, surrounded by pale yellow grass. To the north you can see more tents.

716.description: You are in a small tent-shop to the side of the main area of tents. This tent looks like one of the traders' caravans. Stacks upon stacks of weapons and foo d line the shelves. A warm fire burns in the middle of the floor.

717.description: l You are inside one end of the Chieftain's tent. This looks like a cooking area because there is a large fire in the middle and there is lots of food around the place.

718.description: dagge You are standing inside the Chieftain's tent. It is darker in here than outside but you can still see the sun through the sides of the tent. There is a sort o f kitchen to the east. The room is comparatively well-furnished compared to the other tents.

720.description: You are under the leafy fronds of the palm trees in the oasis. Coconuts hang temptingly from the high tree branches.

721.description: You are on the southern side of the oasis. The ground here is covered in a kind of short yellow grass, well irrigated by the oasis. To the north-west you can see some rocks sticking up from the desert.

722.description: This room does not really exist. If you managed to get here, please go away.

723.description: You are inside the Witch Doctor's tent. Various things are lying around in here like skulls, knives, and bottles of liquids. This tent is almost as decorated as the Chieftain's.

724.description: You are in a small circular area suitable for dancing and generally holding festivals. In some areas, grass is present, and stone seats have been position edaround the area.

725.description: double./A penalty d You are inside a quite large tent. In the middle of the floor is a large cradle obviously used to keep a baby in. This tent is well lived-in with furnishings all around you.

726.description: You are inside a small tent in the village. The tent is fairly bare but there are holy statues lying around. This looks as if it could have been a shrine at one point. ./

727.description: ty double. You are standing to the north of an old bridge. Above you hangs the branches of a small tree. The main village is to the west.

800.description: You are in a corridor which is ankle deep in fine dust. As you walk forward it swirls up in choking clouds around you.

801.description: As you make your way forward, the fine dust blows faster and faster. It seems a sthough a howling gale is blowing through the tunnels. You are starting to find it difficult to breathe. There is a dark cave to the south which might offer sanctuary.

802.description: As you make your way forward, the fine dust blows faster and faster. It seems a sthough a howling gale is blowing through the tunnels. You are starting to find it difficult to breathe. There is a dark cave to the south which might offer sanctuary.

803.description: You are at a junction. A sand-filled tunnel continues west and south, and there are some caves to the east.

804.description: You are in a large cave. As you dust the sand of your clothes, and your eyes become accustomed to the light (or lack of it), you see that the cave is man made. There are smaller caves to the north, east and south. ^X/

805.description: You are in a small cave. Bits of bone and flesh and snapped swords lie around, some of them stuck in unpleasantly mauled corpses.

806.description: You are in a medium sized cave. Thigh bones are neatly stacked in racks along the walls. The floor is covered in dung. It smells absolutely vile.

807.description: You are in a small room. The walls are covered in multi-coloured drapse. A few statues stand around the room - it must be some sort of shrine.There is a notic eboard on the wall.

808.description: You are in a winding sandy tunnel. Strong intermittent gusts of wind blow sand into your face. There are broken arches to the east and south.

809.description: You are standing among stalks of wheat which reach up to your neck,

810.description: This is a totally uninteresting cave.

811.description: You are in a desert like room, with various caves, full of sand.

812.description: You are at a junction with cave entrances all around. There is a wooden board with 'HOUNDMEN'S CONSERVATIVE CLUB - MEMBURS ONLY' painted in blood.

813.description: You are in the houndman party, with many posters on the walls. A poster of Neil Kinnock has been grafitied by some considerate Dog. (God backwards)

814.description: You are in a side room. It is filled with campaign leaflets. Stacks and stacks of them extend into the distance.

815.description: k You are in a cavernous bar. One entire wall is devoted to every conceivable alchoholic beverage. Along the other wall is painted in six foot letters: 'HOUNDMEN'S CONSERVATIVE CLUB - YOU AIN'T SEEN ANYTHING YET (BUT WE'RE WORKIN G ON IT)'

816.description: You are in a bare, dusty room. There is a single desk with a notice on it : 'Campain Officer General'

818.description: Here the corridor is regular and built from stone slabs. An sign pointing east-west reads 'Trollkin. We're goin to kil you. We hayt humanns. GO WAY!!!!'

819.description: You are in the trollkin guard room. It is filthy. There is urine streaked down all the walls, and a large pool of vomit on the floor. A broken table is cover edwith newspaper.

820.description: You are in a trollkin nursery. From here you can see the many vestiges of trollkin education in the arts of torture.

821.description: You are in a central corridor, off which are six rooms. It is disgustingly filthy and the stench is indescribable.

822.description: You are in what seems to be a trollkin bank. The only methods of getting money out of this bank seems to be a good mace (on the head.)

823.description: You are in the guard room of a decidedly disgusting rsection. Of course you can tell that it is a trollkin room as there is a pile of rotting flesh on the flo or.

824.description: You are in the central corridor.

826.description: You are in a trollkin room which is so hideous that I cannot even bring myself to describe. You sit down, staggered that any race could be so depraved. There is a squelching sound. You get up very quickly.

827.description: You are in the chef trollkin's room. It smells like a sewer. Enough said.

828.description: You are in a long steel corridor. To the east is a door marked 'EXIT'.

829.description: You are in a long steel corridor. To the east is a door marked 'EXIT'.

830.description: You are in a long steel corridor. To the east is a door marked 'EXIT'.

832.description: You are in the long lost VELVET HAVEN. Many people thought this room was lost i nthe mists of time. Untold treasure lie in this room. It was created by MARSHAL L DAN DARE THE JELLY KING.

833.description: You are in the Box room. Many boxes lie scattered arround. A door lies hidden behind the boxes.

834.description: You are in a storage room. A naked lightbulb provides the only light. You can hear the sound of dripping water. There is a hatch to the south which leads to a long greased slide. You cannot see the end of the slide.

840.description: You are in a cave in the sand. It is very small and very very hot. There are lots of sacks and empty boxes lying around.

841.description: You are just off the store-room.It is empty.

843.description: You are standing in a large well furnished room.There are leather chairs all over the room and beautiful pictures of naked women line the walls.A diamond statue of Belgarion stands in the middle of the room.The Rivan Sword hangs ab ovethe wall.

844.description: You are in the first room of CONAN the Priest's storeroom.

850.description: Out to the West a glacier snakes its way between steep sided snowy peeks. Streaking its surface you can see the dirty blemishes of moraines.With the ful l force of your situation hitting you,you feel light headed.

851.description: You stand on the Eastern edge of a deep ravine.To the North and south paths lead away from the formidable glacier.The cold bites into you.

852.description: You are north of the glacier trail.Here pine trees cover the mountain side. Far in the distance you can hear the howls of wolves...and it chills you to your very bones.

853.description: This area is a deep depression.To the west is the centre of it.Some kind of structure is at its centre.The ice tower to the West looks ominous indeed.

854.description: A giant ice fall blocks your way.The sky above is crystal blue...You sense evil here.A very wide crevasse is to the east.

855.description: At the centre of the depression is a shrine of ice.

856.description: To your east is a deep ravine.To the North is a dark cave....At the far end of glacier is a high ice Tower,warnings of the mage ring in your ears.

857.description: Further along the glacier you go.The tower is now to your south.Crystalline trees coated in ice stand dead next to you.What evil caused these hardy trees to die?

858.description: You have entered the cave of the heroes.An ice block is positioned in the centr eof the room.Deep inside it is a mirky sword like object.Around the wall is an inscription...'Here the great heroes laid down their weapons for peace'.

859.description: You have moved higher further up the glacier.Mountains lie westward.However a small igloo has its opening facing you just south of here.

860.description: You stand above the land with a great vantage point over the whole land. To the East below which the dungeon must lie are low lieing barren hills.... However just at the limit of vision you can see the sea

861.description: This is a well furnished igloo.Large ice blocks make up the walls.You see a variety of personal effects stacked up on the walls.

862.description: The glacier ends here.The High Mountains of the Soulease begin.South a trail leads to the foot of the Ice Tower though not directly.This area is gloomy large clouds cast dark shadows.

863.description: A huge icefall hangs of a granite cliff here.However ice steps have been cut into it.Icicles fall of at intervals.

864.description: You are standing on weaker ice at the southern end of the lake.To the west is a gravel heap.Further movement west is made difficult by this obstruction.A rope hangs down from mid air here...'MAGIC INDEED'.

865.description: A huge fiery red causeway leads south to the foot of a truly massive tower. Only those above level three would surely have the daring to risk going any further...You hear a rasping noise!!!

866.description: You stand on an iced up lake.The ice looks as though it will support you hopefully.It continues southwards.Steep and unclimable mountains support the valley behind you.

867.description: You are at the head of the ice fall.Some creature lives here and you have woken it up.

868.description: You stand amoung many boulders which rise so high that passage west is impossible.This moraine carries on to the South. CCLIMB/Sslips on the boulders/Ga wound/Touch you slip and hurt yourself/

869.description: The southern end of the moraine is here.You can see a wishing well made of mithril.A good magic prevails here.A sign states go forth and be good beyond the gift. C/

870.description: An ice pavement is leading ever closer to the evil fallic scar.Dread covers you rheart but a quest must be completed.A fluorescent warning says 'IF YOU ARE NOT ON A QUEST LEAVE ... NOW!!'

871.description: The massive causeway widens here statues of fearful monsters accompany the road all the way to the foot of the tower.A trellis of evil weeds hangs overhead.Hi ghin the sky above you a firestorm rages with the full fury of hell.

872.description: You have deviated from the path and are entering the plains of ice and flames. Volcanoes of ice are dotted around this hellish plain.You feel badly out of place here.Further entry is possible to the south.

873.description: A huge plaque stands here to be examined by any passer by.Fiery pits on either side prevent one from leaving the pathway.Evil grips your heart even stronger now.

874.description: You stand on the slopes of an ice volcano.Sulphurous fumes attack your nose here great magic of disruption casts an ugly shadow over this place.Higher and higher the slope rises.

875.description: You stand on a stone pedestal overlooking the barren hills of ZKUL.You long for the security of the dungeon once more.There is a button here.

876.description: At last the foot of the tower no door is obvious here.The walls are made of pure white ice.The flames around shun the walls.High above you can see a windo w ledge...is that a figure?

877.description: You stand on the summit of the Ice Mount.Looking down you see deep rivers of ice.A neat hole is positioned in a rock wall here.

878.description: You are standing on the window ledge of someones bedroom.Your position is rathe rprecarious.

879.description: You are standing in the luxurious bedroom of the princess.There is a massive four poster bed here.Velvet curtains partly mask a large bay window.Two exits provide escape from the room...plus the window.

880.description: You are in a pink bathroom.A humming noise comes from the North where a large wall sized mirror covers the whole mirror.In the mirror you can see yourself refreshed.

881.description: Statues fill adorn this room all around.Pictures of great might adorn the walls You realise that this is the first landing of the Tower.

882.description: Statues fill adorn this room all around.Pictures of great might adorn the walls You realise that this is the first landing of the Tower.

883.description: You are in a bare room...satanic symbols bear ill on the walls around.

884.description: You stand high above the land on a long curved balcony.To the West is room 888.

885.description: You appear to have reached the far wall of the tower.A giant map covers most of the room here...showing nearly all the dungeon domain.

886.description: You stand in the games room,built to amuse the princess.You see that black has ALMOST won.

887.description: This appears to be a rest area.A small poster is pinned onto one wall.

888.description: This area appears similar in most respects to the other games room.You may return from here.

889.description: You are inside Kamthra's crystal tower. This is a large chamber which has a lon gblack-wood table in it. A large padded chair rests at the northern end of the table. There is a large golden mansized mirror in the northern wall.

890.description: You are in a large circular shrinechamber carved completely from pure crystal. A well -stocked bookshelf lines the eastern wall, and a heavy oaken door leads west. There is a walnut wooden table in the middle of the study.

891.description: You are in a stone chamber.
