894.description: You are off the storeroom.South is a funny looking room.

895.description: You are in HAL's storeroom. To the north is the NEW level 10 monster section.

896.description: You are in a empty room. Sometimes used by HAL.

897.description: You are off the store room.

898.description: You are off the storeroom.South is a funny looking room.

899.description: You are in HAL's shrine come temple.

901.description: You are swimming beneath the dark waters of the pool above.Amazed that you have never discovered this area before.The pool widens out to the north.

902.description: You are swimming beneath the dark waters of the pool above.Amazed that you have never discovered this area before.The pool widens out to the north.

903.description: A frozen maggot's corpse You have reached the bottom of a deep pool.Murky waters block your vision. You can just see some shape to the east far off.

904.description: You have swum a long way north and sand banks block any further motion.However it is still possible to swim back south.However carefully sculpted coral gives the impression that something lives here.

905.description: You are swimming in front of the enterance of a dark gloomy cave.The water here exudes an unpleasant feel onto yourskin.

906.description: You are in a large and gloomy cave.Rippling water makes echoes on the cave wall sthese cause creepy shadows to slide along the walls.

907.description: A shipwreck hangs uneasily on the sandbank here.A giant boulder has gashed a deep hole into the wreck.This is the obvious cause of the wreck holding its present position.Inside may present shelter from sharks.

908.description: A fallen statue head~3/Key 320/A long stick of chalk You are on the lower deck of the ship.Here a disarray of boxes heralds the disaster,which overcame the ship.To the north and south are dark areas.A slick mast rises from this place.

909.description: You have swum into the bows of the ship...something has moved just out of eyeshot.

910.description: You are in the stern of the ship.The planks here have rotted away here due to spoiling the ship for a hapeouth of Magic floating dust.

911.description: You stand upon the top deck of the ship.Some steps rise to your south.

912.description: This is the officer's cabin.A shut steel door is inset in the Northern wall. Graffiti adorns the walls .... Ozzy rules...but Mustaine is the law !!

913.description: fungus/A half-rotte You are in the old strongroom of the ship.

914.description: You are high up on the stern area of the ship.Out to see can be seen underwater reefs just beyond the surface of the water above you is the sun smiling down.. .'HELLO THERE IT SEEMS TO SAY.....'...oh my god is he going mad you ask.

915.description: You are in the crews quarters.

916.description: You are in the games room of the ship.

917.description: Zowwwyy!!!!! You have broken the surface of the water.You take a deep gasp of air.You are standing on the top of the crow's nest.

918.description: You are in the Bosun's cabin.....wow how mind numbingly boring...Well TOUGH!!! I couldn't think of anything alright so SOD OFF you berk.

919.description: This is the ships church.A small shrine sits in the middle of the room.From the pictures of The Reverent Moon on the wall you detect that the passangers of th e ship weren't roman catholic.

920.description: You stand in the great room.In the first floor of the pyramidal tomb of Mustapha III.The treasures here will be needed later.Remember no escape except through the capstone.GREAT secrets are here keep them that way.

921.description: You have moved further along the first level of the great pyramid.To the east is a large stone boulder which blocks your way east.

922.description: You are in a small hovel.The dusty passage leads east.A message is inscribed on the ancient wall here...

923.description: You stand in the dark mirky passages of the Pyramid.A long steel rope hangs here from the ceiling.Some extravagant hieroglyphs hide some meaning.

924.description: You stand at the foot of a massive drop which reaches up into the pyramid. A rickety bridge hangs across the pit here...but it looks like a one way trip.

925.description: AAGGGGHHHHHHH!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! no way out......or is there.What is the bouncy ball on the floor for.

926.description: South to return to the land of the living....otherwhise continue up to the ultimate treasury.A steel panel is here.

927.description: There are several physics practicals going on here, quite happily, all by themselves. Somebody has dropped their wallet on the floor, just begging to be examined.

928.description: You are in the technician's bit. An odd technician asks you if you know anythin gabout the sex life of a Van der Graaf generator. The Van der Graaf attempts to have sex with you. For one who isn't easily shocked you find this very shocki ng.

929.description: You are in P7. Larry appears to have stolen this room to pack Trek food in. A sickly sweet smell of Angel Whirl and an overpowering odour of curry assail yo urnose.

930.description: You are in P5. 2Ma are doing a practical. They have constructed an electric sonometer and are playing some funky riffs on it.

931.description: You have entered ACPs room.There is a terminal in TELL on the front bench.

932.description: This is P1. The whole room is vibrating to the sounds of Peter Gabriel I, which are deafeningly loud. Larry bustles around with a bit of admin, bopping to the groovy rhythm.

933.description: This corridor is empty, except for a few cobwebs and an evil-looking spider in one corner.

935.description: This is where the smell of Jaffa cakes is coming from. Somebody has planted a large Jaffa tree here, in the middle of the physics block. Mc Vitie is standin g by the tree proclaiming that you are a Munchkin.

936.description: The corridor here smells of baking Jaffa cakes - Mmmmmmm! There seems to be no apparent reason for the smell, so it's safe to say that you're probably hallucinating.

937.description: You are in the main corridor. Ray Davies is walking his corgis up & down in an attempt to inspire them. His corgis are barking in such a way that it makes yo u want to stand on them.

938.description: You are still in the corridor. North is P3 and south is P4. There is a mess on the floor that must have come from some corgis, so don't step in it.

939.description: The corridor is dark here, but you can just make out Genghis Khan lurking in th e corner

940.description: You are in the electronics lab. A gremlin is wandering around spooking all the apparatus.

941.description: You are in the Sleff theatre. Doc Coyne is showing 'The Song Remains The Same' to a load of people with beards and flared trousers.

942.description: A hefty bloke is standing here outside the Sleff theatre and requests you to show him your Film Soc card.

943.description: You are in Pele, the mild-mannered janitor's hole. There is a load of useless junk on the floor.

944.description: You are in the gents. In one of the toilets is some food, but it looks like it has been here for weeks.

945.description: You appear to have entered the Physics block. To your right is the trek noticeboard.

946.description: You seem to have stumbles into an Oxbridge period. 20 skeletons are seated at desks, still with pens in their hands. Mr Hand is talking about optical instruments, and seems to have bored everyone to death.There is a box on the front desk.

947.description: This is P2. Ray Davies' unruly form lives in here. The room stinks of cigarettes.

948.description: You seem to have entered the strange box and from the inside, it looks much bigger.

949.description: Here you are Steve.You may need some directions: West to

950.description: You are at a dead end with a barred door to the east. Slats in the door allow you to see behind the door.

951.description: You are at the moment in the mages office,A shrine is in the room.

953.description: You are in the second room of the mages storeroom section.

960.description: You have come to a junction. Strange flashing lights and weird noises can be detected from the north.

961.description: The strange goings on that you noticed before are bugging you. The walls here are plastered in a green gunge.

962.description: mall dagge This room is smelly, but not offensively so.It seems to have been inhabited by a peculiar form of dinosaur.There is a locked door to the north.A rope dangles down from above.

963.description: This room, it seems, is the source of all the noise. You see a Bang & Olufsen Hi-fi in one corner churning out Heavy Metal.

964.description: Well, who expected to see him here?

965.description: Well, who expected to see him here?

966.description: Well, as you might have guessed, you have come to a dead end.And that is probably just how you will be soon, DEAD!

968.description: You have arrived at ANDY PANDY'S storeroom.If you continue you will face certai n death.

969.description: You are in ANDY PANDY'S shrine.What a magnificent place this is!

970.description: This room is ANDY PANDY'S bedroom.Lots of cute teddy bears are lined up against the bed.His blue and red striped pyjamas are lying on the floor in a crumpled heap,stained with goodness knows what!!

971.description: This is one hell of a bad place to be if you are lower than level 29.It was a g great mistake to come in here.Besides you have a monster to deal with now!

972.description: You walk into the lair of some strange creature. Paint is splashed down the in various psychedelic primary colours. There is a glass desk in the centre of the room with a single rose in a vase.

973.description: You are in a dark room, the ultra-violet light blinds you but you soon become a ccustomed to it. There is a small Well located to your west in a recess in the wall.

974.description: You are in a smooth cavern. The walls have been sanded and polished, and a neat pile of bones has been tidied away into one corner. A wooden board reads: 'LAIR FOR SALE OR HIRE. DES DET RES. WOULD SUIT FIRST TIME DENIZEN. VACANT ON POSSESSION'.

975.description: You are in the deadliest room in hell - move and you die.

976.description: You are in the lair of some large animal. Various bits of dismembered human hang down from the ceiling. There is a rotted wooden box in the corner.

977.description: You are in a pit. There is a exit to the north, but it is too high to reach. An extremely noxious smell wafts from the south.

978.description: A hideous cathedral soars up in front of you, obscene gargoyles leer at you fro mthousands of alcoves in the stone. A rusted gate to the west stands ajar, a si gnon it reads EYEL HELLPRIEST. There is a small wooden door to the east.

979.description: You arein a small earthy cave. Surprisingly, it is quite cool, and a faint breeze meanders between the blocks of ice scattered on the floor. There is a machine here marked 'ACME VENDING MACHINE MARK 1'.

980.description: You are inside a vast cathedral. It is gloomy and hot, and your brains reels from the impact of pure, complete silence. You can dimly see a figure to the south.

981.description: You are at the centre of the Eyel Cathedral. Above your head, a dome rises several hundred feet. At its pinnacle, there is a tiny window, through which y oucan just see an eye, looking down at you. Narrow stairs lead down to the west .

982.description: estcard You are in a smaller chapel to the side of the cathedral. Rows of seats are arranged in front of a blazing fire in a metal dish.

983.description: You are in the Eyel High Priest's room. It is large and round, and there is a solid gold altar covered in dead flowers. You can hear soft chanting from all around. Scrawled in charcoal on the floor is : CURSED CURSED

984.description: You are in a crypt, beneath the Eyel Cathedral. Several coffins are propped up on the walls, but they are empty. In one corner, a flagstone has been removed from the floor and there are signs of digging.

985.description: You are in a marble entrance hall. A fountain hums pleasantly to itself, and geraniums and narcissi line the walls. Light pours in from somewhere, although there are no windows. There is a door to the north, with a small typed notice : 'KNOCK'

986.description: You are in a wide low corridor. Blasts of scalding air shoot out of holes in th ewall periodically. The corridor get even wider and lower to the east. There is atunnel to the south and a heavy steel ringed door to the north.

987.description: The corridor ends at a huge gate, made from human thigh bones. 'THE SECOND GATE OF HELL' blazes in foot high letters in front of you, but t hegate is locked. To the south there is a shimmering gap in reality.

988.description: You are in a Beautiful Shrine.

989.description: You are in an office. There is a large desk with some papers arranged neatly on it, a telephone, and a telex machines. 'Flight of the Valkyries' is being played loudly from wall-mounted speakers.

990.description: You are in a large sandy arena enclosed by a very high stone wall. It is very hot and the sun beats down fiercely. Someone has writted 'TOADSTOOL IX' in the sand.

991.description: You are in a large sandy arena. Frightened lizards scuttle away as you walk over the white hot sand.

992.description: You are in a hot snady arena.Many people are staring at you!!!!

993.description: You are in a hot sandy arena. 'Only Demidivine Intervention Will Save You' has been chalked on the wall.

994.description: There is a Golden Condom hanging on the wall. Many people haven't used it.

995.description: You are in a small dark room. In the centre is a brass lever. A notice reads: 'Teleport gate to Arena. Please note that all combat is to death. People who wander in by mistake will be left to die. Further details from Gerbil.'

996.description: You are in a corridor. A bright neon sign proclaims 'HI THERE! ARENA THIS WAY!'

997.description: You are in a sandy arena. Jeering crowds surround the pit, but the 12' walls clearly give you no chance of escape - you will have to fight your way out!

998.description: Behind a lot of loot, surrounded by a feverish glow, there is a shrine, probabl ybelonging to David.

999.description: You are in the annex to David's office. A sign reads 'Only authorised personnel to the East - Fun for all to the West.'

1000.description: Hewn from an ancient mine, with dwarven tools, stand the Gates of Moria; ageles ssymbols of Durin's kin. Engraved into the heart of the rock are long forgotten runes.

1001.description: You walk into a small passage with other passages running in nearly every direction. This room smells of musty dank air.

1002.description: Doom covers this area....will you ever see the fair fields again...If you are less than level 3 then probably not!!!

1003.description: Here the passage ends in a large chamber.A tomb is in the centre of the room. A large cover is locked into place on the top of a sarcophagus.

1004.description: The passage bends here and you feel yourself walking deeper underground.The light here is reduced.

1005.description: Two corridors meet here.A torch hangs on the wall here.This sends light to the whole area.Acid dints on the floor show evidence of a recent presence here!

1006.description: You are in the main guards room.They stand in front of a western opening.A chest here posesses a large mithril lock.

1007.description: A sentry post is here.But it is no ordinary sentry post!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

1008.description: This is a room.BUT WOW ITS REALLY BIG MAN I MEAN ....H U G E!!!!

1009.description: There is a wooden guilitine here with an exceptionally blunt wooden blade. Hence the messy corpse...they should have bought a Wilkinson Sword.

1010.description: You are in the hill giant's living room.There is a small television set in the corner.On the T.V. is the favourite program Grange Hill Giant.

1011.description: This is a long passageway.Intricate stone carvings adorn the walls....A note is tagged to the wall here.

1012.description: You are in the hill giant's kitchen.Giant spoons,spatulas and other implements line the walls.A huge window on the Northern wall casts light into the room.

1013.description: You are in a small stone chamber.A well trodden path leads to the steps in the middle of the room...a memo says 'DARE YOU ENTER LEVEL 2'.

1014.description: This is the guards bedroom.Three giant sized beds....well smelly old matresses are lined up on the floor.Small tea chests are at the end of the beds.

1015.description: You are in the chief giant's throne room.A golden throne is bolted in the centre of the floor.Tapestries adorn the wall.

1016.description: This is a giant's swimming pool.A small path will enable you access north and south.

1017.description: A small drainage pipe runs from the north here to the south into the pool.A gurgling noise of excreta running down the pipe makes you cringe.

1018.description: You stand in the bowl of a giant's toilet.Poooooooooooooooooooooo!!! what a stink.Something is inside.

1019.description: You are at the bend in the passage here.Routes lead east into an old store. Also there is a smooth retreat to the north.The ceiling here is quite low about seventy feet!

1020.description: You are in an old giantish store room.The walls here are not dusty..and not long,dark,musty,wide,narrow,smooth,stone,flat,cold,wet,damp...so sod off all ultra boring room descriptions.

1021.description: An unfinished room so youll have to wait

1027.description: You are in another teleport gate.South to return.East to the castle,West to the Underground and North to the village of Argand.

1030.description: You have appeared in a glittering shrine.You have the dubious privilege of having been chosen to explore (and try to survive) the BATTLEZONE.

1031.description: You have arrives in the infamous (well,it will be soon) BATTLEZONE.Only one person can get out alive.There is a noticeboard here.

1032.description: As you progress deeper into the battlezone,you see many strange and fascinating objects.You are bewildered and can feel a headache developing.

1033.description: You have entered the lair of a crippled battlezoner.He's a bit tired but very angry.

1034.description: This room is totally uninspiring except for a dangling rope.

1035.description: Things have gone from bas to worse.'Nuff said.

1036.description: This excuse for a cess-pool can only be described as that which a sewer rat might throw upat the sight of!

1037.description: You have arrived outside the gates of a factory.Sweet smells greet you.

1038.description: Well done!Now you have got a clear head,you may continue,but will need to prepare yourselves for the fight ahead(If you last that long!).

1039.description: You have come to a bend in this dank and dusty corridor.

1040.description: Wandering west,you come to a right hand turn.Corpses litter the floor.

1041.description: Venturing north you find yourself in a dank and smelly corridor.

1042.description: This corridor smells of excrement. From the west, whirring noises of many machines can be heard from the east.

1043.description: This is the central shrine of this stage.Weird machines line the walls.

1044.description: The corridor bends here to the east.The whirring noise can only just be heard.

1045.description: The noise of machinery to the south is getting on your nerves.Perhaps you should do something about it.

1046.description: This room is very wet and you have to step carefully to aviod getting your feet splashed. A distant rumble can faintly be heard.

1047.description: This room smells surprisingly clean and fresh.

1048.description: So you think you're clever eh? Well,try this section for size.

1049.description: You have entered the abode of The Chief Battlezoner. He's very angry.

1050.description: You are at the end of a corridor.

1051.description: You at a junction in a corridor.

1052.description: You are in a small room. There is a door to the north.

1053.description: You are in a small room.

1054.description: You are in a small room. There are doors to the south and east.

1055.description: You are in a small room. There is a door to the west.

1056.description: You are in a corridor running east-west.

1057.description: You are in a large cave.

1058.description: You are in a small cave.

1059.description: You are in a small cave.

1060.description: You are in a small cave.

1071.description: You are outside the Storeroom of Iain Richardson.

1072.description: You are in a misty passage running north - south.

1073.description: You are in a dark misty passage running north - south.

1074.description: You are in a dark misty passage running north - south. There is an exit leading east to the Storeroom in paradise.

1075.description: There is a strange feeling of loneliness and rejection in the air. You feel unwanted.

1076.description: You are lost in a forest of stunted pine trees.

1077.description: You are lost in a forest of stunted pint trees.

1078.description: You are lost in a forest of stunted pine trees.

1079.description: You are lost in a forest of stunted pine trees.

1080.description: You are lost in a forest of stunted pine trees.

1090.description: Don't ever be this corrupt again !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

1104.description: You find yourself at a junction of several corridoors. The air here is conditioned, and the walls are made of smooth pannels which are giving off soft white light.

1105.description: There are storage lockers on the southern wall here, alongside a notice proclaiming 'Section built by Paul Roxby. Please do not vandalise.'

1106.description: This is obviously a kitchen. There are many types of food preparation machines arranged about this small room, while silent conveyor belts can be seen bringing food.

1107.description: Air suspension seats cover the floor of this quite large room and large viewing screens cover one wall completly. A door marked 'Works Entrance' leads off to the North, and carries an electronic combination lock.

1108.description: The passage leads to some leisure and restaurante facilities. To the East is a heavy titanium door marked 'Armoury' which has large hydraulic mechanisms mounted above it.

1109.description: This corridoor continues for quite a distance. Several photographs adorn the walls, and you notice that they seem to change every few minutes. Some of the pictures appear to be advertisements.

1110.description: A small plastic security card Accomodation rooms lead off from passages to the East. Unfortunately the ends of these are protected by forcefields. A security camera scans the air around you, whiring quietly to itself.

1111.description: Searing pain flashes up your arm as you desperately try to escape from the forcefield. Your eyes hurt with the blinding light searing your retinae, even though your eyelids are tightly shut.

1112.description: You approach the door, which grinds open for you. Stepping into the room you can see multiple high-tech weapon racks covering the walls, and laser projectors mounted in the corners which track your every movement.

1113.description: To the North is a restaurant, but a voice-lock protects the door to it. The food would probably be inedible to you anyway. To the east is a door marked private, while a door to the west has a slot, above which 'Use Card' is wtitten.

1114.description: This room is lavishly decorated, and contains a silk covered bed against one wall. Some treasure chests lie in one corner, while many leather volumes are stacked neatly on ivory shelves.

1115.description: You are standing at the Southern end of a very long corridoor. Grapheti inscribed on the walls proclaims 'Sinha and Pallin are ace!' This is obviously in very bad taste.

1116.description: You are standing in a cave, set into a high cliff. To the south is a very long, draughty corridoor, while to the west someone has hung a flimsy rope bridge which leads to an island.

1119.description: You enter the catacombs. It is dark and cold. A chill wind blows gently around, but there is a trace of mustiness in the air. An old, faded notice reads 'Catacombs built by Paul Roxby, May 1987.'

1120.description: You are in a large pentagonal room, a kermit (yes a file transfer protocol) sit sin one corner. There is a large box (pdp 11-70??) in one corner with a sign sa ying insert token.

1121.description: You are in a smelly cave. What remains of a block of charcoal is now consumed b y a livid flame.

1122.description: You are in an ancient shrine. Many icons are hung on the roughly hewn walls and a sphere in the centre of the room glows with soft green light.

1123.description: You are standing at a crossroads in the catacombs. To the south is a holy room, and by the west wall is a slot marked 'Insert Exit Pass from higher things.'

1124.description: You are in a new room, do not be alarmed; Ostrogoth's section is not yet finished, but this does mean that a couple of the less exciting special cases have been removed.

1125.description: You are at a junction. A strong breeze blows here, while on the wall is a large circular picture with a bar protruding from behind it.

1126.description: You are in a small cave, with a granite pedestal, with a wooden pad on top.

1127.description: You insert your exit pass and the door slides open. You walk through it and find yourself in a small room with velvet covered walls and floor. To the west is an exit.

1128.description: ewspaper/S You are standing at a junction. A ventilation hole blows air into the room and a rope hangs from the roof.

1129.description: You stand at an underground junction in the catacombs. A deaf badge-maker sits at a stool on the hard floor.

1131.description: You walk along the low passage. There is a damp musty smell here, and a series of knife blades line one wall.

1132.description: paper/A badg The corridoor turns here. Along the walls is a row of torches, which seem dim compared with the others in the catacombs.

1133.description: You are by the exit to the catacombs. A high rock door blocks the way to the west, but an Arabian Knight seems unpeturbed.

1134.description: You are in a hidden part of the catacombs where the Greatest warriors and mages lay down for the last time. A cold wind blows from somewhere. The secret door is still open if you want to get out.

1150.description: You are in the largest, most stunningly beautiful cavern you have ever seen. The entire cavern is filled by a huge golden 'C' five hundred feet high, surrounded by a circle of solid diamond. An archway leads east.

1151.description: An iron gate blocks the way west, but through its bars you can see a row of offices with initials like DDPC and JCDS on the doors. To the south there is a small crack in reality.

1152.description: You are in a small room with fifteen perfectly smooth onyx walls. Voices whispe rfrom hidden corners. On a small metal plate on the floor is engraved: 'COPYRIGHT DAVID QUEST 1986,1987. All Rights Reserved.'

1153.description: You are in a large room, decorated with books, and memorabilia connected with 'The Hitchhikers guide to the galaxy. Mohit Dutta's autograph is scrawled on each wall.

1154.description: You are in 'Milliways', the restaurant at the end of the universe. To the north you can see the terraces, where lunch is currently being served, to the West, the bar, and to the East, the kitchens.

1155.description: You are in the bar. A barman is mixing all kinds of cocktails.

1156.description: You are in the chamber of the kinky leather goddesses. Those who dare succeed, and those CENSORED - MD. - Why do people always edit my rooms!!??^

1157.description: You are on the terrace of 'Milliways', at the end of the universe, looking out into space.

1158.description: You are in the kitchens. The staff are too busy to notice you - the universe is going to end in a few minutes, you know!

1159.description: You are entering 'the Heart of Gold' spaceship from the west end. No respon- sibility whatsoever can be accepted for los or damage to characters etc.

1160.description: You have entered one of the infinite improbability sects. At the moment, probability is normal, but things could get worse! To the north you can see what appears to be another improbability chamber.

1161.description: Wow, this room is really wild! A voice over the loudspeaker says 'Improbability is 1 in 100". To the East, you can see the bathroom and toilets.

1162.description: You are in Gent's toilet. There seems to be something revolting leering at you from under the seat. There is a slot in the wall.

1163.description: You are in the women's toilets. What a pity that the only woman on the ship is a humanoid!

1164.description: You are in the hypergalactic luxury bathroom. The walls are papered with gold- wall paper. In the corner is a locked cabinet.

1165.description: You feel somehow strange. Suddenly your arm disappears - at least this can't get much worse. A voice booms "Probability 1 in 100,000" - quite harmless, bu t fun! To the north is 'the Final chamber', and to the east, the Intergalactic airport.

1167.description: You are in an immaterial room, where matter reins over mind. Suddenly, both your legs vanish, but you can still feel them.

1168.description: You are in the control room. Many useless artifacts lie here, including some computer called 'Eddie'! To the west you see the translation office, and to t he east a Vogon ship. To the south is the rest of "The Heart of Gold".

1169.description: Welcome to the translations office. A sign reads "Spligod helugerithm". Perhapps a translator could come in handy??

1170.description: You are in a dark room, with slimy walls on a Vogon ship. Human organs lie everywhere. You can go north to see the Vogon chieftain, or west to the crossroads.

1171.description: This is a fairly revolting room. It has pictures of Neil Kinnock on each wall. The Vogon chieftain begins to recite poetry - good job you can't understand him.

1172.description: 4/An automatic Bov This room is filled with pictures of food and drink. A sign above the entrance reads 'Robot feeding centre'. South to the prehistoric domain, east to the robot repair centre, or north to the control room.

1174.description: This is the robot repair centre. There is a conveyor with a button next to it.

1175.description: You are in what appears to be a common room, a sign next to the one that tells you this reads 'If you do not have a specific reason for being here GET OUT'

1176.description: You are at a large juntion. To the north there is the common room, to the East is a demi-god test room, you view is obscured in the other directions by a thi ckhaze.

1177.description: A man with pointed ears stands at the center of this room next to a long windy conveyor belt. In one hand he has a pile of white tablets, he offers you one.. .

1178.description: To the west a sign reads Ostrogoth's office. Against the west wall is a MB2, well at least it works!, from where you are standing you can just make out something on the screen, it looks very interesting...

1179.description: You are in a large room with a palm tree in its centre swaying gently in a breeze that you cannot feel. There is a sign on one wall: 'Od;smf yr;r|pty' T here is a notice board below this sign.

1180.description: This room appears to be a large field. Dispite this there is a man wearing a pi nstriped suit sitting behind a desk. There is a sign on his desk saying 'J.Clea se', he looks very worried...perhaps he has forgotton his lines.

1181.description: You enter this room and at first feel very happy, it is decorated reasonably, but then you begin to feel uneasy, there is a long, slightly curved wooden can e by one wall, above it there is a sign 'Dvjpp; yr;r|pty hsyr'

1182.description: There are many daises around room, on each there is a statue of a great figure; Ostrogoth, Vizigoth, Morpheus (depicted as a hedgehog).There is a button below which there is a sign saying 'Do you wish to fight a demigod?'

1183.description: This room is very cold, there appears to a be a steady wind blowing from one en dto the other, on one wall there is a large circle with a line through it. Eith erit was painted by a drunk decorator, or it is daubed in blood.

1184.description: As you enter this room you are blinded by an array of colours, reds blues green sand yellows merge and melt away around you.

1185.description: On one wall there is what looks like a shear exposed rock face with a multitude of metal pins stuck in it, around the floor there is an assortment of pieces o f mountaineering equipment.

1186.description: me food You are in a shrine dedicated to Ostrogoth (the barbaric...fight if you will). There is a pile of treasure here.

1187.description: You appear in front of the 'Robot demigod' (eat your hearts out Sirius Cybernetics Corporation). You appear to have disturbed his meal,so make it qui ck\TRDD NIYYPM to get out.

1188.description: You have entered Ostrogoth's secretaries office. There are four golden phones one of which is ringing.

1189.description: Clearly Ostro's voice made you temporarily shift out of existance. You recover and find you sitting on top of a chandalier. You reckon that you could probobl y jump down without killing yourself.

1190.description: You are in a candelabra. A thick wire protects you against falls.

1192.description: You are outside storeroom 1193. All is shiny and new, pristine in its novelty. There is a rotting corpse in one corner.

1193.description: You are in a strange persons room all people mmust quack....

1195.description: This is the storeroom of Arthur the great, returned back to life after his p prehistoric era. Watch where you step, the floor is very slippery!

1196.description: You are outside the pleasure dome.

1197.description: This is the new arena. Instead of the old stone walls there is a new energy field surrounding the fighting arena. Crowds jeer at you just beyond your rea ch.

1198.description: This is the annex to the storeroom of Arthur the Great.... need I say more??

1199.description: You are outside Sputnik's office.Bitter sweet fumes creep out at you from the door keyholes.But just look at that guard.Big,blonde and dressed in red leathe r armour.WOW! 2/

1200.description: You are in an office of a recording studio. A deck is on the other-side of the room it suddenly leaps at you.

1201.description: A shadowy stair can be seen climbing steeply upwards. No light penetrates the upper steps.

1202.description: The passage arches here, with a level floor leading into the dark. An odourous smell hangs in the air and the floor begins to creak. An old staircase descend s from the south wall.

1203.description: The floor continues, rising gradually through the darkness; and you now hear th efaint patter of accompanied by the monotonous sounding of a large drum.

1204.description: The route widens and you feel a chill wind strike your face. The way forward is blocked only by several fallen boulders.

1205.description: Here stands a wide arch opening into three passages; the northern passage leads down, the southern one climbs up while the east-west passageway seems to run o n smooth and level ground.

1206.description: Still climbing, you pass a large round hole like the mouth of a broken wa

1207.description: The passage winds steadily upwards, as far as you can judge in great mounting curves. As it rises, it grows wider and loftier. There are now no more galleri esor passages on either side.

1208.description: The route widens through some arched doorways into a black and empty space. Vaguely you can see many mighty pillars hewn of stone continuing to the east. ./

1209.description: This great hall continues to the west and divides to the east. Three other entrances can be seen; one straight before you eastwards, and one each side.

1210.description: A wide north-south corridor runs here, a glimmering light comes from a doorway to the east. The stone door stands on square doorposts.

1211.description: This is a small chamber, dimly lit by a wide shaft in the further eastern wall. The light enables you to see a single oblong block of white stone; inscribed i n which are dwarven runes, 'Balus son of Fundin, Lord of Moria'. It seems to be quite solid.

1212.description: The passage plunges straight down, great iron rings are attached to the walls here. The stairs above begin to crumble and broken stones begin to roll down t hestairs from above. It seems to be quite unpassable.

1213.description: The stair is totally dark and unlit. You manage to grope your way down a long flight of steps then look back to see nothing. However you can hear the louder crashings of falling stones.

1214.description: The stair ends here, and joins an east-west corridor. Large shouts can be heard to the west accompanied with the solemn ringing of a drum. The way east become s hotter but apparently safe.

1215.description: Another archway stands here adjoining a long hallway. The humid atmosphere contained within makes you sweat; a torchlit corridor continues to the east.

1216.description: The corridor turns to the north and west through an ageless cemetary, large bodies lie on the floor.

1217.description: The passage ends here. Before you to the north, lies a wide abyss, spanned only by a thin white marble bridge. Here stands an ancient evil.

1218.description: The passage continues to the north. To the south lies a bridge crossing a wide abyss, which falls many leagues below. Several humanoids with yellow skin dwel l here.

1219.description: Hewn from ancient stone, with dwarven tools, lie the Gates of Moria. The doors stand slightly ajar, but need a great strength to move them.

1220.description: The passage runs further downhill, narrowing slightly. The ground is littered with all sorts of objects, but it seems to be passable.

1221.description: The passage stops here, in front of a large locked door. The wooden door is splintered and has several (probably obscene) orcish letters daubed in blood-r edpaint on it.

1222.description: The chamber has not been used in a long while. Green slime hangs from the walls ,the air is musty and several rodents have made this their dwelling place.

1223.description: The passage twists and turns through solid rock, becoming very monotonous. Unusually several small footprints mark the dust-covered floor.

1224.description: The route widens and you can hear eerie noises in the darkness around you. It may only be a trick of the wind in the cracks and gullies of the rock wall, or perhaps there is another reason?

1225.description: The tunnel meets a sheer drop, which falls into a shallow trough at the bottom of a long hard slope. The tunnel runs southward through the rock away from danger.

1226.description: The tunnel opens to join a large hall faced with marble. There is a large stone door in the east wall, and a passage turns off to the south where a loud cracking sound can be heard. Several humanoids guard this place waiting for intruders.

1227.description: The chaamber is fairly small, curtained off with embroidered hangings and strew nwith skins; three humaniods sit at a table.

1228.description: This gallery begins to sway, with the rocks grinding and cracking about you. Several large fragments shatter away from the ceiling and rain down towards yo u.Something is burrowing through this place.

1229.description: The route narrows and the air becomes odourous. You can see several sulphurhole sin the walls of the passage. To the east you can hear large cracking noises. T o the south the passage branches.

1230.description: The road passes this way sloping downwards to the west; the rock walls remain featureless and you can hear distant voices.

1231.description: The roof-arches which run east along a torchlit corridor, to the west a blue mist blocks your vision. The room contains the usual amount of detritus along with some humaniod bodies.

1232.description: The corridor links another chamber here. Your vision is hindered by a blue haze ;the chamber contains nothing of real value and the walls seem to be fairly sol id

1233.description: This gallery has not been used in a long while; the floor is lined with dust an dcob-webs. Several stone blocks have fallen from the roof; but you still catch sight of a crude chest, rotting away.

1234.description: The passage becomes more humid; you feel a warm breeze blow through your hair a syou walk forward to a T-junction. Small humaniods dwell here.

1235.description: The passage ends to the north, whereas to the south several orcish cries can be heard; you feel the heat of a natural fire, hot enough to melt the stongest ir onitself!

1236.description: This passage becomes hotter to the west, to the east it is lit by torchlight; i nthat direction several drums can be heard beating.

1237.description: This place seems quiet. Before you is a crude altar surmounted on a mahoghany dais. Above the altar is a statue of a three-headed orc. There is a well lit chamber to the west.

1238.description: You are at the edge of the river. There is a bridge here crossing the river. Th etemple is to the south. Across the bridge you can see some forests.

1239.description: You are in a forest of pine trees. There are trees in every direction.

1240.description: You are in a forest of pine trees. There are trees in every direction.

1241.description: You are outside the Okazaki Castle of the Shogunates. There is an open door to the north. A few samurai warriors are practising. A river is to the west.

1242.description: A river runs under the castle here. The castle is built upon a steep cliff. The castle walls tower above you ominously. There seems to be no way into the cast leFrom here you can see that there are many forests around the castle.

1243.description: You are at the corner tower of the castle. Some of the samurai armies are gathering to the north. To the west you can see an entrance into the castle.

1244.description: The main entrance into the castle is to the west through the portcullis. Samura iwarriors are practising their skills here. There are some huts to the east. There is a path leading down off the cliff to the north.

1245.description: You are on the pathway leading up to the castle. You can see it towering up to the west. Samurai warriors are fighting here. To the north is a small hut.

1246.description: You are inside a peasant's hut. A straw mattress lies in the corner next to a small wooden table. There is a small shrine here where the peasant usually pra ysThere is an open doorway to the south.

1247.description: To the south is a large hut. The path continues to the east-west. To the e^Aast you can smell some smoke and you see a river. The Okazaki Castle lies to the west, where some samurai are fighting.

1248.description: You are inside a large hut. The kitchen is to the east. There are some wooden stools around the table. There is a weaving loom here.

1249.description: You are in the kitchen. Utensils are placed neatly on the table and the shelves .Some dinner is cooking on the smll stove in the corner.

1250.description: You are at the river. A bridge crosses it here. There is a cave to the north an dcharred remains of past adventurers lie scattered about the place. A sign read s 'BE..RE .HE ...GO.'. The rest of the message is obliterated.

1251.description: You are in the dark cave. A musty smell is carried by the breeze. Scorched remains lie around the floor.

1252.description: You are in a corridor running east-west. There is a portcullis to the east. The walls are decorated with paintings and ornate tapestries. There is a large hal l to the west.

1253.description: You are in the main hall. There are many paintings on the walls. To the north are the ante-chambers leading up to the throne room. The storerooms are to the west. An open door leads south out of the castle. A long corridor is to the e ast

1254.description: You are in the storerooms of the castle, sacks of grain and wheat are stacked neatly on the floor. A door leads east into the main hall. There is a trapdoor set into the middle of the room.

1255.description: You are in the ante-chamber to the throne room. Benches are lined up on each side of the room. Some servants are praying at a small temple here. The throne room is to the north.

1256.description: You are in the throne room. To the north is a large balcony window overlooking the whole cliff. In the middle of the is a golden throne. On the walls are man y valuable paintings. There is a small shrine in the corner of the room.

1257.description: You are on a ledge halfway down the cliff. The track leads westwards down the cliff and south upwards. You can see one of the castle's high towers above you .

1258.description: You are at the base of the cliff. The castle rises high above you. There are some strange marks on the cliff-face. High above you, you can see a balcony window. To the north is a large sea. Fisher-men are trying to catch some fish here.

1260.description: You are flying through the air (with the greatest of ease), the wind is rushing round your ears (SE direction 58 knots). Unfortunately you fall out!

1261.description: Fortunately there is a haystack on the ground to break your fall, (well you can see a yellow mass on the ground rushing towards you).

1262.description: Unfortunately that brown speck in the middle of the haystack now mutates itself into a pitchfork :- HINT I suggest that you do something pretty quick ... that ground looks real mean!

1263.description: Fortunately your frantic writhings to avoid instant impailment (a very painful and traumatic experience, unless you happen to like that sort of thing) lead y outo miss the pitchfork.

1264.description: Unfortunately a combination of your frantic writhings, Ruth washing her hair, and a nordic demigod in a particularly bad mood, you also manage to miss the haystack.

1265.description: You pick yourself up, you do not feel to bad considering that you have just fal len somewhat in excess of 3000 feet. You shake the dust from your arms, legs, hair....In the distance you can see a bar....You have a terrible sense of Dej a vous.

1266.description: You are in the enterance to the colloseum. To the north is the arena. To the south is the street. To the east and west are stairs.

1270.description: If you end up here either a demigod has sent you here, or else someone has bee nvery nasty. DO WHAT YOU ARE TOLD!!!!

1271.description: You are in room 2 of the test area!!!

1272.description: You have reached the end of this corridor, REMEMBER: THERE IS NOONE MORE HELPLE STHAN THE ONWNER OF A SICK GOLDFISH!!!

1277.description: You are entering the monster section for level 10+

1278.description: You are in the monster section.
