1294.description: You are in the study of the gerbil. A small desk adorns the room

1295.description: You are in a small hovel in ^Athe bookcase. A sign reads WEST to the s-h-r-i-n- e.

1296.description: You are deep in the bookcase

1297.description: You are deep in the bookcase

1298.description: You ar in a small shrine dedicated to the GERBIL

1299.description: You are in a recording studio microphone and musical instruments line the walls .

1300.description: You are in the silver spaceship.

1301.description: You are at the corner of two streets. James Street is to the East, where most o fthe shops are. To the South is Cassedy Street. A sign reads 'Eric Clapton shot the Sherrif'

1302.description: You are outside two shops in James Street. The General Supplies Store is to thw eEast, and the weapons shop is to the South.

1303.description: You are at the counter of the General Supplies Store. The woman at the bar is adjusting a sign saying 'Deposit Returned on empty bottles. A storeroom is to the South.

1304.description: You are under a large a large wooden arch. There seems to be a small room built into the top of it. You could probably climb up to it, with a bit of luck.

1306.description: You are in the weapons store. An old man is oiling rifle barrels behind the counter. Guns only cost a dollar.

1307.description: You are in the storeroom of the General Supplies Store. Boxes of groceries and other goods are stacked up against the wall, in a neat order, largest at the t op.

1308.description: You are in General Custer's office. A candle is on the empty desk, illuminating piles of documents and papers.

1311.description: You are in a small house. There is an oil-lamp in the window, but the house is empty. The owner is clearly catholic, as you can see from the small shrine in the corner, draped with rosary beads.

1313.description: You are in a small side-street. There is a Saloon to the South, and the double doors are still swinging after someone has just gone in. Horses are tied up outside it, on a wooden bar.

1314.description: You are walking down a dirt track between two rows of wooden buildings. To the East is a door with a sign over it saying 'James Gibbon M.D.'

1315.description: You are in the cellar of a small house. Some stairs lead North to the rest of the house. There are no windows, and the only light in here is from a candle stuck in an empty bottle.

1316.description: You are in the Sherrif's office. It is also the stolen goods office. The Sherri fis looking in particular for some stolen jewellery.

1317.description: You are in the Saloon. The barmaid has lost her purse, and is willing to trade some food for it. There is a gang of sleazy cowboys playing poker in the corner .

1318.description: You are walking down a road. A small dirt track leads North, and a path leads East.

1319.description: You are walking down a grassy path. The main part of the Fort is to the West. You can see the cemetery way down to the South, along the path.

1320.description: You are in the doctors surgery. From the instruments on the walls, you can tell that he isn't a very good one, hammers, chisels, kitchen knives etc.

1321.description: You are in a large field. There are many cattle milling around here, being rounded up by a mounted cowboy.

1322.description: You are in the backroom of the saloon. There are lots of crates of bottles, ful land empty lying against the walls.

1323.description: You are in a small wooden room built into the arch. There is a door to the Nort hwith a strange orange light coming from around the doorframe. To get down agai n,you will need a long ladder, because it is too steep to get down otherwise.

1324.description: You are on a small path. There is a small wooden sign pointing South saying 'Boot Hill.' A path branches off to the East, with daisies growing on it.

1325.description: You are outside a cattle ranch. A field full of cattle is to the North, and the house is to the East. A road leads to Sanson Street, to the South.

1326.description: You are in a two-roomed house. The bedroom is to the East, and the front door i sto the West.

1327.description: You are in the bedroom of a one-roomed house. There is an open window to the South, which you could easily climb through.

1328.description: You are at the top of Boot Hill. There are lots of small wooden crosses marking the graves of the people who have been buried here. To the South is Sanson Street.

1329.description: You are in Sanson Street. To the North is a cattle ranch.

1330.description: You are in Sanson Street. There is a faint aroma of cows in the air, and it seems to be coming from the Northeast.

1331.description: You are in the middle of Sanson Street. There is an open window to the North, leading into a bedroom, which looks very easy to climb through.

1332.description: You are in Sanson Street. A path leads North to Boot Hill. You are outside a jewellers, with a broken window. The jewellery has been stolen.

1333.description: You are on a small path. There is a path leading to Boot Hill to the West, and to the North is a ranch.

1334.description: You are in a stable courtyard. There is a stable to the East.

1335.description: You are outside the tack shed, which is to the East. To the South is the stable courtyard.

1336.description: You are outside Davy Crockett's ranch. He is sitting on the steps of his porch, smoking a hand-rolled cigarette, and drinking from a brown bottle.

1337.description: To the North is a field full of cows, and there is a house to the West.

1338.description: You are in the South-West corner of a large cattle pen. There are lots of cows rubbing up against your legs, in the hope of being fed.

1339.description: You are in the field. There is a cattle crush to the North, with a cowboy branding cows in it.

1340.description: You are in the field. A cowboy in a felt hat, green bandana and levis is branding cattle next to you.

1341.description: You are part of a huge cattle pen of about 15 acres. There is a locked shed nex tto you. It has a very small lock, so you will need a small key to unlock it.

1342.description: You are in a stable. There is a young lad here brushing down a fine black stallion.

1343.description: You are in the tack shed. One wall is devoted to bins of feed for the horses while the others are filled with sadles, bridles, brushes, curry combs and oth erinteresting horsey objects.

1344.description: You are inside a small wooden shed. There is a locked door leading outside. Thi sis where Davy Crockett keeps his savings, and has hired a mean looking guard.

1345.description: You are in the forest. Trees are all around.

1347.description: You are by a ruined shrine. Valuable bits of marble lie around. Some times an old lady comes to put flowers by the Statue.The room could be called a temple.

1348.description: You are in the forest. Trees are all around you.

1349.description: You are in the forest. Green trees are all around you.

1350.description: You are in the forest. There is a swamp to the east. There is the smell of ozon ein the air, and some of the trees are burnt. Could this be the work of demigod s?

1351.description: You are at the sundial, however some vandal has broken it so you cannot tell what time it is.

1352.description: You are in the engine room. Machinery is all around. The deck is south.

1353.description: You are in the swamp it is knee deep and continues to the east and south. There is a sundial to the west. You can feel something around your feet.

1354.description: You are in the swamp. It is waist deep. It is difficult to move.

1355.description: You are in the forest. The swamp is to the east

1356.description: You are on the bridge. There are knobs and dials everywhere, most appear useles showever a big red button lures invitingly.

1357.description: You are in the hold of the ship. There are fish all around you packed in ice. The hold continues to the west. The deck is up.

1358.description: You are in a forest. There are some foothills to the west. You can hear the sea to the east.

1359.description: you are in the hold. This is where they package the fish in ice.

1360.description: You are in Manchester Bridge club(in the bar). You are playing bridge.There are many people about.

1361.description: You are at the south western end of asgard, high above the normal realm of man. A dark tunnel leads west into nothing!

1362.description: You are at southern end of asgard.

1363.description: You are at the southern end of asgard some way to the north you can see an impressive building.

1364.description: You are at the southern end of asgard. To the south can be heard strange noises .

1365.description: You are at the south eastern end of asgard. A sign read 'Aldred'

1366.description: You are in asgard. Home of the gods and visiting place for plebs.

1367.description: You are in asgard.It spreads out before you in all directions.

1368.description: You are on the plains of asgard. To the north lies the impressive home of the gods VALHALLA.The building is made out of pure gold and from Midgard (earth) it is often mistaken for the sun.

1369.description: You are on the plain of asgard high above the rest of the universe.It is covere d in mist which means you can't see your feet.

1370.description: You are at the eastern side of asgard.You can see the largest builing in existance also a sign reads 'Aldred'

1371.description: You are on the western side of asgard. A bridge made from solid gold goes west to a place where the law is taken seriously!

1372.description: You are in the monastery there is a holy portal here for priests.

1373.description: You are in the entrance hall to VALHALLA for the momen but it is closed to mere plebs.

1374.description: You are in Asgard.To the west is VALHALLA home of the gods.Some way to the east you can make out the shape of a building so large that your mind flips even considering it.

1375.description: You are standing next to a brige going eastwards.Into the largest builind in creation A sign reads 'DEMI DEVINE PRODUCTIONS' Nuff said I think. You are by the way in asgard

1376.description: You are on the western side of asgard but a little bit juts to the west

1377.description: You are in asgard. You get the feeling important people live here!

1378.description: You are in Asgard. To the south is a golden building called VALHALLA. It is the home of the gods. There is a very impressive gateway leading in made of a diamond twenty metres high with a hole through the middle so that you can wal k in.

1380.description: You are standing next to a large bridge going east to the largest building you have ever seen. A sign on it reads 'DEMI DEVINE PRODUCTIONS'

1381.description: You are at the north western corner of asgard. A crystal bridge goes north to a land where people wear a lot of togas!

1382.description: You are at the northern end of asgard.It goes for miles south from here..

1383.description: You are at the north of asgard. A bridge leads down to a island to the north.

1384.description: You are at the northern end of asgard, there is a bridge going north to some form of temple.

1385.description: You are at the north eastern end of asgard. There is a temple to the north and a blackness to the east.

1386.description: You are in asgard. To the east is a golden building, the famous home of the god s and supplier of quality beer VALHALLA

1387.description: You are in the enterance hall to DEMI DEVINE PRODUCTIONS.It is very grand you get the impression you should be very quiet!

1388.description: You are in the ground floor of DEMI DEVINE PRODUCTIONS.

1389.description: You are on a very dangerous cliff edge. Try north or south but do not expect to live.

1390.description: You are in a fantastic shrine dedicated to ARTHUR the Great.Be careful where yo ustep as the floor is very slippery

1391.description: You are in the office section of DEMI DEVINE PRODUCTIONs Every where is made of gold and silver and purple silk.

1392.description: You are just off asgard, to the north all you can hear is one big party!

1397.description: You are outside the Storeroom of Iain Richardson.

1398.description: You are in the storeroom of Iain Richardson. KEEP OUT

1399.description: You are in the SIN BIN !!!!!!

1400.description: You find yourself on a roof overlooking the city. Across the way on another roo fa woman is bathing in the nude. The place has a strange resemblance to the old city of Morreemo Half.

1401.description: The woman bathing in the nude looks strangely enticing. A tap is lying on the floor, and hot water is gushing out. The bath is almost overflowing. TSTART/1/

1402.description: There is an old worn stone staircase by your side, and light shines in through the painted glass windows with various pictures of authors on them. A heavy wooden door is to the west

1403.description: You are in a room with a large wooden bookcase full of catologues. There is a door into a room to the west which is at an angle to the wall of about 120 degrees. A window next to the entrance room faces out onto a crumbling church .

1404.description: The door to the east is angled at about 60 degrees to the wall, and a look through the window reveals some fields with people working them. There are boo ksmainly about languages in this room.

1405.description: This room is shaped like a wedge of cheese with the pointed end cut off. The door to the north is slightly angled to the wall. The room contains books abou t cultivating and cooking food, and from the window you can see a road.

1406.description: The window seems to face open out onto nothing from this room, but far below yo ucan see some clouds and fields. It is as if you are looking out of a window in an immense cliff. A message on the ceiling reads : Geometry matters !

1407.description: This room has no windows, but it does have an oddly angled door which leads to the west, and a normal one to the north. It has a wall between the two doors, and a bookcase against it. There is a table with a shut, chained up book on i t.

1408.description: From the window you can see some rocks far below. The books in here are about history.

1409.description: The door to the west is at an angle to the wall, and there is no window, but instead some holes in the wall which let in some light and a draught.

1410.description: There is a window in this room, and from it you can see dozens of monks rushin gabout on carefully laid paths. The door to the south is angled to the wall in a strange fashion.

1411.description: This room has a window opening out onto a shallow courtyard, and 6 other w windows can be seen.

1412.description: This room contains books about weather in it, and two of the doors are at an angle to the walls they are on. A window faces a courtyard.

1413.description: This room contains many books about writing books and drawing pictures, but most of them are chained up, and a few lie open on a table. There is a spooky feeling about the room.

1414.description: There is a painted glass window here, and most of the four oddly angled walls are covered in books concerning religion and religious things. The atmosphere istense.

1415.description: There is no window here, but one of the bookcases has a conspicuous gap where there should be a book, but there is a white panel.

1416.description: There is a window here, and the door to the east is at a steep angle to the wall. The books in this room are about music, and there are manuscripts on the table.

1417.description: From the window you can see the courtyard and there are some towers on the opposite sides.

1418.description: There is no window here, so you can't see anything.

1419.description: You are in a bank. There is a closed vault here.

1420.description: You are in DINKY DURKY PLAZA it is very busy.

1421.description: You are on a ledge.You may be able to climb up.A dark and scarey tunnel leads north.

1422.description: You are in the treetops. The view from here is absolutely underwhelming.

1423.description: You are in a treetop. You are surrounded by colourful parrots and other birds. It is possible to go south into another tree.

1424.description: You are in the treetops. From here you can see the island in all its glory with the mansion, beach and lagoon. You can even see a sunken galleon off the south of the island.

1425.description: You are in the treetops. Someone has carved the following message into the tree trunk - 'Fly Demi-divine Airways Limited, contact your local travel agent for further details'.

1426.description: You are in the treetops. Someone has carved something into the tree - 'Help me, HELP ME ! The green banana ! THE GREEN BANANA !!!!!!!'. Obviously he/she was totally insane.

1427.description: You are in a small slimy cave.It carries on eastwards.

1428.description: You are in DREDD's apartment it is a shrine to the law. There is a sign which reads 'the LAW is everything'

1429.description: You are in the badlands. Radioactive waste lies all around.

1431.description: You emerge from the darkness of the evil forest onto one side of a bright clearing. The trees here are massive and seem to glow like gold. You can see carved into the side of one tree a small sign.

1432.description: You are on a forest path. Around you trees rejoice in the glory of life. There is a smaller path off to the east and to the north you can see a large cross-roads.

1434.description: You are at a cross-roads in the forest. To the north the trees seem brighter as if they were even more glad to be alive. There are paths to the south,east and west.

1435.description: You are on a forest path. The trees are large and healthy and the path is airy.

1436.description: You are on the forest path. Up ahead to the north you can see a crossroads and the path continues to the south.

1437.description: You find yourself at a cross roads in the forest. To the west the path improves as it seems to have been made out of some form of black stone. To the north yo u can see a small hut.

1438.description: You are outside a small hut. On closer inspection you see that the hut is made from ebony, oak and mahogony inlaid with gold and platinum. It looks of if mad e by one of the Gods. A notice on the door says - please knock.

1439.description: You come upon a small clearing. You realise that you are now on the borders of the domains of the faeries. It is said that any which enter more often than no t go completely mad.

1440.description: The path bends here. To the south is a magical clearing from which you can glimpse the radiance of what looks like a golden statue.

1441.description: You are in a shrine dedicated to ISTQU The Benevolent. Faeries and pixies flit around your head and feet respectively and you are overcome by the general feeling of peace.

1442.description: Yoy follow the path of dark stone. Vague unease settles over your stomach and you realise it is due to the total absence of any forest sounds.

1443.description: You follow the dark path. However in the distance to the west you see a strange dark citadel. You know that you shouldn't enter it however the temptation is strong - aided by a strong magical field surrounding you.

1444.description: You realise where you are. You are standing outside the infamous citadel of Bla'k-g,rth. Here the Gods of evil are worshipped and sacrificed to. There is a small sign here.

1445.description: You stand in the enterance hall to the citadel. The very air seems blacker here and a strange force seems to compress your chest.

1446.description: You find your self in the library. The charge of magic in here is quite incredible and you feel you hair go on end.

1447.description: You are in a magical passage. Lights flash across your eyes and the strain on your chest becomes worse.

1448.description: You are walking along a darkened corridor. Torches with black flames light the way and you can here a ritual chanting.

1449.description: You find yourself at the end of the corridor. To the north is a door inscribed with strange symbols and to the west is a door inscribed with even stranger symbols.

1450.description: You find yourself in a large office. Magical tomes whirl around your head threatening to beat your brains in.

1451.description: You fall into a deep pit. The walls seem unscaleable but on the wall is a message from Istqu telling you that you may escape by defeating the demon and praying to him.

1452.description: You find your self in a dark shrine. A deep shaft descends from the middle of the room as if to hell itself. This is a place of evil.

1460.description: Welcome to ISTQU PLEB DISPOSAL SERVICES LTD. Any high level interferences catered for - our aim is to kill, maim, rob, annoy and please.

1461.description: You are in a discreet side office for special visitors. Installed here for thos ebusy adventurers around town is the newest in luxury FROGHOP gates.

1462.description: You are in a reception area containing comfortable seats so that business may b ediscussed in a relaxed atmosphere. There is a silver bell on a small table in the corner as well as a noticeboard on the wall. There is a locked oak door t o the north.

1463.description: You are in the deposit room. Here deposits and required payments may be left. You should note that none-payment of any debt will result in termination with extreme prejudice.

1466.description: There is a crowd of girls to your left in the middle of them is the Dwarf Hero ALVIN and he is telling them about his battles with great and nasty monsters. H e does not notice you unless you attack him.

1467.description: You are near the throne of SAGA The wife of ODIN. She is quietly chatting to on e of her maids when she catches sight of you and welcomes you in the name of he r husband to VALHALLA. You bow in respect.

1468.description: You are standing in front of the great ODIN, the whole court stands still and q uiet, you quickly kneel before him and then suddenly the whole court is alive a gain!

1469.description: You sit down by an empty table and order a mug of ale when BALDIR The brave sit s down and starts talking to you, when he asks you if you would like to place a little bet at arm wrestling ???

1470.description: On the right of you is a pet dragon bound to the wall by a heavy metal chain(NO T MUSIC), you decide to walk over him, but as you get close he tries to bite yo ur hand off !!!

1471.description: You get talking to one of the Guards of the Hall, the Guard's name is BOGGI The Dwarf and he tells you that LOKI and HELA are here today which is a rare thing .

1472.description: You are standing next to the strongest of all the Asgardians, THOR The Thunder God, he is ODIN's first son and the wielder of MjYou are standing next to the s trongest of all Asgardians, THOR The Thunder God, wielder of Mjolnir.

1473.description: You are standing in a secret room behind ODIN's throne. This is where his bigge st and strongest bodyguard stands on watch, waiting for any enemies of the real m.

1474.description: You stumbled upon LOKI attempting to play a practical joke upon BALDIR the Brav e. As you have stopped him having soem fun he has decided to kill you for a bit of sport.

1475.description: You are in the darkest part of the Hall as the Death Goddess Hela is here and s he is using some of her powers to make it look more like her home.

1476.description: You are now at the bottom left hand corner of the Hall, eating on his own is a small Dwarf. He offers you some food if you will stay a while with hom.

1477.description: On the floor is a drunk giant named RANKLE, he is sleeping at the moment, but h e could wake up at any moment! You had better be careful.

1478.description: Sleeping before you is the meanest and maddest giant there is around if he DOES wake up he will probably kill you.

1479.description: Standing to the left of you is LOKI's bodyguard KRANK he is the cleverest of al l the giants and the bravest. On the floor is a large bag of gold coins... Mayb e you could get them...

1480.description: You are in the wine cellar tied up in the corner of the room is a small girl ca lled Mary... Hela has tied her up for being so happy.

1490.description: You are in the new improved battle zone. In one corner of the room there is a machine dishing out forms for the food vendor.which is in another room. A sign says ask nicely....

1491.description: You are in the new battlezone.

1492.description: You are in the new improved battle zone. New rooms would be entered here.

1493.description: You are in the food vendor room. A sign reads ----A Form is required for the food---- -- just give me the form --

1497.description: You are outside istqu's storeroom. A cool wind blows from the south.

1499.description: You are in the bank vault the door is closed.

1501.description: You follow a dark and meandering path through the undergrowth. Paths leave to the West and the North, and you might be able to hack your way South.

1502.description: You are on a path that is leading some one to the password

1503.description: You have reached a junction. The main path continues to run North-South, but to the East there is a small path leading to a well-kept hut, surrounded by a ver y attractive flower garden.

1504.description: @6 You are in a small neat house. The old crone who lives here is running a shop, selling food and amulets. There is a shrine fixed to the wall here, but you do not recognise the God portrayed.

1505.description: You are in a faerie glen. In the centre is a mushroom on which the faeries are gaily cavorting. They invite you to dance with them.

1506.description: You are in a large, open, well-lit clearing. Someone has evidently been here be fore you, since there

1507.description: You have hacked your way through the dense undergrowth to arrive at the base of an ancient tree which dominates the landscape. The main path continues to the North and South, and you can see a small path to the East.

1508.description: You are precariously perched at the top of a huge tree. From this vantage point ,you can see the entire canopy of the forest, punctuated by a scattering of sma llclearings, and a semi-ruined building to the North.

1509.description: The path widens here, and there is a small break in the forest canopy, letting in a few rays of sunlight, giving dazzling illumination to the path, to either side of which you can hear faint animal noises.

1510.description: The path now has a branch to the East, which quickly bends round to the North. You can see coloured lights and hear faint music off the path to the West.

1511.description: You have arrived at a crossroads. The road to the North is blocked by an Ogre who is demanding &5 (that's the unit of Ogre currency). Since you cannot pay, soyou'll have to force your way through.

1512.description: You are in a twisty maze

1513.description: You are in a twisty maze.

1514.description: You are in a twisty maze.

1515.description: You are at the new barrier so now you must show an even bigger pass than before !!!!!!

1516.description: You are in the middle of a east-west corridor.

1517.description: You are in a narrow corridor.

1518.description: You are at the end of a corridor.

1519.description: You are in a narrow corridor.

1520.description: You are at the western end of a corridor.

1521.description: You are in a empty room.

1522.description: You are at the end of your quest all you have to do is show your pass.

1523.description: You are in a hell hole.

1524.description: You are in a hell hole.

1529.description: You are in the enterance to the mansion.It seems strangely larger inside than outiside. A corridor goes a long way north. There is a large sign which read s 'Have you seen a JUDGE lately'

1530.description: You are at the entrance to an extensive cave system. Slimy corridors lead off i nall directions. Above you, you can see a small square of light. c/

1532.description: You are at a T-junction. The passage to the East and West is joined by another from the North. There is slimy growth on all the walls, behind which can dimly be seen ancient carvings.

1534.description: You are in a small cramped cave. Passages lead off to the North and East, but you cannot stand up in them. The sound of rushing water can be heard to the Ea st

1536.description: You are outside a none existant storeroom.This storeroom is unbelievably boring .

1541.description: You are at the end of a small tunnel, or at least you can't go any further. You can see something glinting in the tunnel to the North, however.

1542.description: The walls of the cave are well-worn, smooth and polished. The walls look as if they have recently been cleaned. You can see a small depression on one wall, slightly discoloured.

1543.description: You are in the priests storeroom. Boring though it is...

1545.description: You are in a beautiful serene place..A sign reads anyone using the facilities does so at their own risk no responsibility will be accepted by the Demi-devine productions ltd.

1546.description: You are at the gateway to many places...

1547.description: You are in intense pain. You feel as if you have had the skin of your hand flayed off and had it dunked in a bath of acid, through which a huge electric current is being passed (it's not nice).

1548.description: You can go whereever you like from here...

1549.description: You are at the southern end of paradise...

1551.description: You are on a tree-lined road.To the south you can hear the sound of frogs.A glowing teleport gate surrounds you.

1555.description: You are inside David'shrine office. If you are less than level 29, then I advise that you leave rather quickly.

1566.description: me food/A huge sword You shouldn't be here, and if you are, you wont be for long.

1567.description: This is bob's stpreroom, so if you're here, bugger off. Oh, by the way, if you know the password you can get to my section from her e.

1568.description: There are a plethora of doors here(4, actually)and maybe a hidden on e And the password is a special case.

1569.description: This is the start of the animal chain....this is the dog room.

1570.description: s You are in the bird room...A bird flies from the tree.

1571.description: iamond throne~3/A di Going south from here will take you back to the pub....dont go south if you want oodles of lovely treasure.

1573.description: This room looks like a teaching room of some kind..perhaps there is something to be learnt from these adventures...

1574.description: This is the 'Caps lock room'. Here resides a Caps lock.

1575.description: Following the keyboard theme, this is the 'yuiop room'. Have a nice day.

1577.description: This s a very nice room, very pleasant and calming.

1578.description: this is, a dark, dank, and nasty room. It scares you silly. It scares your pants off.!.

1579.description: This is the treasure room..Why dont you kill the guard and get the treasure . The room is lined with chests & other treasure containing devices.

1580.description: This room is devoid of anything.

1581.description: This is a room that would frighten even the hardiest adventurer. It is the room of a derranged madman.Have fun!!

1582.description: This room is decorated with beautiful tapestries and shields and glorious weapons, as might adorn a temple. The swordsman looks as though he might have been taught how to fight by the defensive guru, John the Hero.

1583.description: This is a drab area, inhabited by the (almost) invincible and (fairly) feared 'The end of a corridor'. It won't kill you (probably)...You won't kill it (almost definitely).

1584.description: You are standing in a large room off the main part of the pub.This is a kind of shop where you can buy various goods from traders.There is an entrance to the pub to the west.

1585.description: This is another barren room, from which this section's shr-ine may be reached (if you have the right know-how ??!?

1586.description: Another inventive room description....Have i said this...What a good section i have designed.

1587.description: This is "bob's shrine room". Here you may deposit treasure etc etc.

1588.description: This is a pleasant room...actually full of greenery and trees.Many shrubs and plants are growing here.

1589.description: This is the first room in Bob's section. You may not pass through unless you are at least level 7. Have fun.

1590.description: This is the fight room. Fight or die

1591.description: Lamp-post making factory. BERTIE's corpse rots in a corner.

1592.description: You are in Mike's basic ACOL lesson. He frowns upon you for mentioning Sputnik doubles. Your partner deals and opens 1NT. What do you bid with the followin g: S: AQ9732 H: 954 D: QJ9 C: Q

1593.description: This is a room containing a NOTICEBOARD

1594.description: This is another part of the illustrious Manchester Bridge club.It is Monday nig ht and there is a pairs competition in progress.Who is likely to be sitting nor th on table six?

1595.description: You are in the GANDALF deletion centre.

1596.description: You are in ISTQU's storeroom. Not much is kept here as he is so powerful that he makes what he wants as he needs it. Really it is a temple to austerity.

1597.description: You are standing in a clearing in a beautiful pine forest. Pixies and faeries flit around your head and run around your feet. However the centre of attentio n is a massive golden shrine in the centre of the glade. A sign says - do not g o west.

1598.description: You are in the punishment wing for non-mages. Please don't try to escape.

1602.description: You are on the edge of a dense forest, next to a semi-ruined temple. There are some stone steps to the north, which lead up to some large oak doors at the to p.One of the doors is slighty ajar.

1603.description: You are at the top of the steps. From here you can see that a forest spreads out to the south, east and west. The large oak door to the north is slighty ajar.

1604.description: You are in the entrance hall of the temple. The roof has collapsed and is now lying on the ground around your feet. There is an open door to the north, and other doors to the east and west.

1605.description: You are in the eastern side-chamber of the temple entrance hall. It has a larg esquare foot bath along its eastern wall. Presumably for an ancient foot-washi ngritual.

1606.description: You are in the Western side-chamber of the temple entrance hall. It has a larg esquare foot bath along its western wall. Presumably for an ancient foot-washi ngritual.

1608.description: You are standing in a narrow east-west passage. It is very cold here!

1609.description: You are in a cold,dark east-west passage. There are some stone steps to the so uth and a passage north.

1610.description: You are in a cold, dark east-west passage. There are some stone steps to the so uth and a passage north.

1612.description: You are in a cold, dark, narrow passage. To the south the passage widens, to north is a low arch, there is a blue shimmer across it. A sign on the north wall states 'ACME patented Ghost Trap - see your local ACME store for details .'

1614.description: You are in a very dark, very cold high cavern. You feel a presence all about you.

1620.description: To the west there is a dark narrow stone passage, while to the north is a well- lit shopping mall. The room you are in is a meeting room for shopkeepers. Chairs line the sides of the room and shopkeepers occupy them. A sign states : 'NO FIGHTING'

1621.description: You are inside a rather plain-looking cell. The only light in here comes from the small open window which is high up on the wall - too high for you too reac h. ir??

1622.description: You are outside a rather plain-looking shop on a well-lit shoopping mall.

1624.description: You are outside an antique shoop on a well-lit shoopping mall. There is a huge wrought iron fence on your left and half a notice hangs from a small hook. It says 'ACME gh... see your lo... '.

1625.description: You are in a small antique shop.

1626.description: You are outside a small taverna in a well-lit shopping mall. It is called The Laughing Gong.

1627.description: You are inside The Laughing Gong. There are several people around the side of the room. Many of them are drinking.

1630.description: You are at a wide bend in the corridor. There are advertising hordings round the outside of the bend, advertising bread, meat, etc. A dark stone passage leads east from here and a well lit shopping mall can be seen to the north.

1631.description: You are in a shoopping mall, outside 'Meaty Meats, the Butcher'.

1632.description: You are inshopide 'Meaty Meats, the Butcher'.

1633.description: You are outside the 'Temple Bakery' on a well-lit shopping mall. A sign on the huge wrought-iron fence on your right states: 'ACME patented ghost traps - see your local ACME dealer for details. Beyond the fence you can see a pile of skulls.

1635.description: You are outside a candlestick-maker's shoop in a well-lit shoopping mall.

1636.description: You are inside the candlestick-maker's shop.

1640.description: You are in an exit shrine.

1650.description: You are in a small square room. Voices can be heard through the doors to the north. They are closed, but don't look locked.

1653.description: You are in a long narrow room, with a large mahogany table in the centre. Ther eare chairs scattered around the room, and doors of all different colours aroun d the walls. To go through one type the colour of the door.

1700.description: You are in a stone walled corridor.To your east is an exit and to the North is the Pyramids of Wonder.

1701.description: You are in a plush,velvet room, Pillows are scattered about the floor as though a fight has just occured. A Body lies in the corner of the room.

1702.description: You are in a long room which outspans to the edge of a cliff. At the end of the cliff there is a long rickety Bridge. The bridge spans a huge gourge.

1703.description: You are aproaching the Pyramids of Esyatacath. The Chariot of Cleopatra lies on the disused road protected by the Royal Guard. A Trumpet sounds from within t he Pyramids

1704.description: Here stands a great hall. Carved into the walls are various egyptian runes whic h can be read easily. Various objects are scattered around the room.

1705.description: You are in The Far Northern Room of the Pyramids. The Riddle still Exists.No-on e can yet solve the riddle of the Sphinx, which will be your only Help!

1708.description: You are in a Cylindrical room. This room seems to change in size as you blink. There is an altar in the middle of the room and an apprentice Wizard is practic ing his spells.

1710.description: You are inside a Palace.The Walls are surrounded by gold and silver tribulates. A Large feast lies on the table.

1711.description: You are in a shrine, plushly decorated with Jewels.There is only one exit to th e east, but there is a river of gold running through the middle of the Room !

1713.description: You are standing next to a circular Pool. Gold medalions seems to float on the bottom of the Pool. A Gold Medalion is lying on the ground

1714.description: You are in a dead end.The room seems to change in brightness as you blink. Ther e is a pile of Old Swords lying in a corner but they seem to have a green glow.

1715.description: You are in the Exit. The walls shine with brightness, as the sun gleams through the northern Doorway.

1716.description: You are in a Room of emense power. The walls seems to quake with fear. You begi n to wonder where you are ?

1718.description: You are in the Sacred Chamber of Toolose. There are two exits available but bfr om both you can hear sounds of talking.

1719.description: You are in A Dark Dismal Desolate Room. An Atmosphere of Magic, realms within t his room. The

1720.description: You are in the Quadrilitic Room.You have done well so far, but the riddle still remains unanswered.

1721.description: You are approaching a dead end. You can see one trader begging for you to buy s omething from his shop. This is a subtle Hint.

1900.description: You enter the castle of JEFANOA, the one time King and now God. Please leave an ygifts in the sahrine on the second floor.

1901.description: You are walking down the corridor, when you come to a bend. The corridor seems to lead somewhere.

1902.description: You walk down a narrow corridor, examining the passage for any secret doors. Th ere are none that you find, so you continue on your way.

1903.description: You walk up the large stairs, conscious of the feeling of dread that fills the air.

1904.description: A footman takes your coat off you, and demands your invitation to the party. Yo uhad better produce it !

1905.description: A Tall, Black, and Strong footman stands, waiting for your invitation.

1906.description: You are on the outer edges of the ballroom floor. Please watch shoes with grit caught between the grips.

1907.description: You are on the edge of the ballroom floor. You turn away hastily when you see the glare off the polished floor.

1908.description: You are on the outer edge of the ballroom floor.

1909.description: You took your shoes off so as not to scratch the beautiful floor.

1910.description: A Rope/ You are still sliding around after taking your shoes off. You get the feeling you will never be able to stand still again.

1911.description: You do a cartwheel, and land on your feet, you flukey ***.

1912.description: You are still sliding around, severely annoyed. The guests feel that way too.

1913.description: You are still sliding around. You are getting fed up.

1914.description: You think you can stand still at last, but sadly fall over. Try some crampons.

1915.description: You climb up the stairs, and see in front of you a man leaning over a banistair ,doing something increadibly nauseous.

1916.description: You can tell this must be a really exciting party, as a young man is throwing u pover the railings. You contemplate suicide after seeing what is coming out of his mouth.

1917.description: Ladder You walk around the walls here, aware of the thinness of the walls surounding you.

1918.description: On the walls are torches of various decriptions. What looks like a nuclear powered torch hangs by a hook, with a label 'DANGER, origins unknown.'

1919.description: You walk up another flight of stairs, hoping to encounter a pink bunny. Your wish isn't granted though, as you see only a little tame white muskrat.

1920.description: You have wandered up a flight of stairs, and realise that you could have gone through a doorway if you had gone up the other flight. So much for energy savi ngsponsored by the labour party (downstairs.)

1921.description: You are in the hallway of what seems to be the sleeping area of this castle. Yo ucan tell this from the servants pushing past you to try and place drunks on th e beds before they wake up.

1922.description: You are going through what seems to be a small, but compact 26 century bedroom. How this came here is a mystery. Maybe explanations would be rewarded with a little something.

1923.description: You are in a slightly larger bedroom than before. Everything here is as you expected it to be, hole-in-the-ground, granite wash basin and sand for soap.

1924.description: You are in a short corridor, lined with weapons from what seem to be zulu wars.

1925.description: Why did the medieval architects build joined bedrooms ? Because the aristocracy like Gang Bangs.

1926.description: You walk into a small chamber, with an arch leading off to the east, but it has been bricked up, obviously with the intention of hiding something.

1927.description: You look up and see a trap door in the ceiling. It has a well used look. On the floor are wear marks where somebody places a ladder.

1928.description: Above the exit in the east wall is written 'Please watch hole in floor, esp. if afraid of heights.

1929.description: As you enter this room, you quickly throw yourself at the south wall, when you notice the hole in the floor to the north. Traces of blood line the edges of t hehole, as if someone decided to jump ...

1931.description: Various torture devices lie scattered on the floor, covered in blood, guts and gore. They obviously have been used recently. You hear a scream coming from somewhere above you.

1932.description: You carefully walk round the far edge of the hole, after peeking down three floors.

1933.description: You step carefully round a bear trap that someone has lain on the floor. To the east you see a strange shimmering, as if there was a time warp there.

1934.description: You look out of a hole in the wall, which looked vaguely like an archery slit. You have ample evidence of this when you trip up over a grinning skull, with a n arrow sticking out of its eye. Funny, I remember a man called Harold ....

1936.description: A slit in the wall matches that at the other end of the corridor. You can imagine the subtelty of the man who built this castle, when you realise that t heslits have the angled walls the wrong way round ...

1937.description: You are walking down a long, sombre corridor. You strip up occasionally on what seem to be bones.

1938.description: As you walk along, you hear a sudden snap, as if you had activated some kind of mechanism ...

1939.description: You can see a hole in the ceiling, with a rafter marked with wear marks.

1940.description: You look up, and see an arangement of pullies, obviously designed for achandelier. But maybe it has another use ...

1941.description: You are in a non descript room, obviously used for food storage. Have you read Stranger in a Strange Land lately ? Do.

1942.description: As you enter this room, you notice the stone pedestal, with something on it. A sign says 'His majesty's favour.' No doubt a reference to Jefanoa.

1943.description: You are in THOMAS COVENANT's retreate. Beware his wrath if he should find you here. Oh by the way, watch the playful royals downstairs !!!

1944.description: You are in a round tower with a small fire in the centre of the room. The walls are bare except for a large tapestry depicting a dark figure astride a white horse.

1945.description: You are in the catacombs of the castle. An important looking guard is defending the key to the next room.

1946.description: You are in the catacombs of the castle. You found the last guard too easy, so try this one.

1947.description: You unlock the door and walk through. You notice a strange little piggy bank, i nthe corner.

1948.description: At last ! You have at last made it into the vault. Rest in peace, and know that you wounds shall be healed, as you fill your pockets with the treasures of JEFANOA.

1949.description: The treasures of JEFANOA lay in front of you, piles and piles of opals,rubies and diamonds.

1950.description: More and more treasure lies scattered around you. You begin to realise that there must be a trap around ....

1951.description: You walk down a long path, with sheer edges going down for a mile or more. You slowly beging to loose track of time, and arrive hours later at a gate to a fort.

1997.description: As you step into this room, you feel a shrinking sensation. You slowly become small enough to climb into the shrine, and do so. Here you see a button.

1998.description: THOMAS COVENANT Weapon supply room. Unbelievers Rule O.k. You see one of those modern portable shrines lying in the corner, protected by a White Magic shield .

1999.description: food/A~ You are in a room which invites death.
